text: Rumination disorder is a type of eating disorder that is characterized by the effortless regurgitation of most meals following consumption. It has the exact synonym, Psychogenic rumination.

Budd Chiari syndrome is a type of hepatic vascular disease and has an exact synonym, hepatic vein thrombosis. It is defined as a hepatic vascular disease characterized by a spectrum of disease states, including anatomic abnormalities and hypercoagulable disorders, resulting in hepatic venous outflow occlusion.

text: Fissured tongue is a type of tongue disease that is also known by several exact synonyms, including Congenital fissure of tongue, Congenital plicated tongue, Fissure of tongue, Fissure of tongue, congenital, Furrowed tongue, Plicated tongue, Tongue, Fissured, geographic tongue and fissured tongue, lingua plicata, and scrotal tongue.

Hypertensive heart disease is a type of heart disease that falls under the category of conditions that, at minimum, manifest with the symptom of high blood pressure. It is defined as a heart disease that is specifically caused by high blood pressure.

@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:abnormal_pupillary_function rdfs:subClassOf :pupil_disease .
text: abnormal pupillary function is a type of pupil disease.

Benign hypertensive renal disease is a type of renal hypertension, and it is exactly synonymous with hypertensive renal disease, benign. Additionally, it is precisely synonymous with hypertensive renal disease, benign, without mention of renal failure.
Laryngostenosis is a type of laryngeal disease and it is exactly synonymous with Stenosis of the larynx.
Recurrent corneal erosion is a type of corneal degeneration and it is exactly synonymous with recurrent erosion of cornea and recurrent erosion syndrome.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:corneal_abscess rdfs:subClassOf :deep_keratitis .
text: corneal abscess is a type of deep keratitis.
Corneal deposit is a type of corneal disease, and it is exactly synonymous with Deposits - cornea.

Adie syndrome is a type of syndrome defined as a neurological disorder affecting the pupil of the eye and the autonomic nervous system. It is characterized by the presence of one eye with a pupil that is larger than normal and constricts slowly in bright light (tonic pupil), along with the absence of deep tendon reflexes, usually in the Achilles tendon. Additionally, Adie syndrome is exactly synonymous with Adie's pupil or syndrome, Adie's pupil syndrome, Adie's syndrome, and Holmes-Adie syndrome. Adie syndrome also has an exact match with the MESH identifier D000270.
Oculomotor nerve paralysis is a type of third cranial nerve disease, which is precisely known as III nerve palsy, IIIrd nerve paralysis, or third cranial nerve paralysis.
Bowman's membrane folds or rupture, which is a type of corneal disease, has the exact synonym Bowman membrane folds or rupture.

Chandler syndrome is a type of corneal dystrophy that is defined as a corneal dystrophy characterized by corneal edema, iris atrophy, and secondary angle-closure glaucoma. This condition is caused by an inflammatory or infectious insult that leads to the endothelium's failure to pump aqueous humor from the cornea, resulting in fluid accumulation, microcystic edema, and angle-closure glaucoma. It has exact synonyms including Chandler's syndrome, Dystrophy of corneal endothelium, Endothelial corneal dystrophy, and Posterior membrane corneal dystrophy.

Fuchs endothelial dystrophy is a type of corneal endothelial dystrophy characterized by the accumulation of focal outgrowths (guttae) and thickening of Descemet's membrane, which leads to corneal edema and loss of vision. It is also known by its exact synonyms, including FCED, Fuchs' corneal dystrophy, and Fuchs' endothelial corneal dystrophy.

Acute serous otitis media is a type of acute transudative otitis media and is defined as an acute transudative otitis media with thin, watery, and sterile effusion. It is also exactly synonymous with acute non-suppurative otitis media - serous.

Acute allergic serous otitis media is a type of acute serous otitis media and is categorized as an allergic disease. It is characterized by being a condition that includes at least some allergic reaction as a symptom. Furthermore, acute allergic serous otitis media is defined as an acute serous otitis media caused by an allergen.

Chondrocalcinosis is a type of arthritis and is also referred to as calcium pyrophosphate deposition disease or pseudogout. It is defined as an arthritis that has its material basis in the accumulation of salt crystals located in a joint. This condition is a type of something that at least has some arthritis as a symptom.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:hypertensive_retinopathy rdfs:subClassOf :retinal_disease .
text: hypertensive retinopathy is a type of retinal disease.

Retinal vasculitis is defined as a type of vasculitis that is characterized by inflammation of the vascular branches of the retinal artery. It shares a commonality with diseases that have symptoms of inflammation and is considered a type of retinal vascular disease. It is specifically associated with the intersection of conditions classified under vasculitis and diseases that are located in the retina. The symptoms of retinal vasculitis include a painless decrease in visual acuity, visual floaters, a dark spot in vision, a decreased ability to distinguish colors, and distortion of images such as linear images.

Neurocirculatory asthenia is a type of somatoform disorder characterized by heart disease symptoms without any identifiable physiological abnormalities. It is also known by several exact synonyms, including cardiovascular malfunction arising from mental factors, cardiovascular neurosis, Da Costa's syndrome, and Krishaber's disease.
Listeria meningitis is a type of bacterial meningitis, defined as a bacterial meningitis that has its material basis in an infection caused by Listeria monocytogenes.

Listeriosis is a primary bacterial infectious disease that has a material basis in Listeria and Listeria monocytogenes. It is transmitted through congenital transmission and vehicle-borne ingestion transmission. The symptoms of listeriosis include backache, nausea, headache, diarrhea, fever, vomiting, and malaise. It is defined as a disease that results in infection, is caused by Listeria monocytogenes, and can be transmitted by ingesting contaminated food or raw milk, or through congenital methods. Ingestion of Listeria by pregnant women can lead to symptoms such as nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, fever, malaise, back pain, and headache. Moreover, maternal infection with Listeria can result in chorioamnionitis, premature labor, spontaneous abortion, or stillbirth. Listeriosis is also known by its exact synonyms, Infection by Listeria monocytogenes and Listeria infection.
Streptococcal meningitis is a type of bacterial meningitis characterized by its material basis in streptococcal bacteria, according to its definition.

Cauda equina syndrome is identified as a type of syndrome and also as a type of peripheral nervous system disease. It is equivalent to an intersection of something that is a syndrome and something that is at least a disease, having a location in the cauda equina. The definition of cauda equina syndrome involves an acute loss of function of the lumbar plexus, neurologic elements (nerve roots) of the spinal canal below the termination (conus) of the spinal cord, highlighting its classification as a peripheral nervous system disease.
Phlyctenulosis is a type of keratoconjunctivitis and has exact synonyms Phlyctenular keratoconjunctivitis and Strumous ophthalmia.

Riley Day Syndrome, also known precisely as HSAN III, familial autonomic nervous dysfunction, and familial dysautonomia, is a type of hereditary sensory neuropathy. It is defined as a hereditary sensory neuropathy characterized by a wide array of symptoms including gastrointestinal dysfunction, gastroesophageal reflux, vomiting crises, recurrent pneumonia, seizures, gait abnormalities leading to loss of ambulation, kyphoscoliosis, postural hypotension, crises of hypertension, absence of fungiform papillae on the tongue, decreased deep tendon reflexes, defective lacrimation, and impaired perception of pain and temperature. The syndrome has its material basis in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the IKBKAP gene (ELP1) located on chromosome 9q31.

@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:functional_gastric_disease rdfs:subClassOf :stomach_disease .
text: functional gastric disease is a type of stomach disease.
Bladder lateral wall cancer, which is a type of urinary bladder cancer, is exactly synonymous with both "Lateral Wall of Bladder" and "malignant neoplasm of lateral wall of urinary bladder."

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:ring_staphyloma rdfs:subClassOf :scleral_staphyloma .
text: ring staphyloma is a type of scleral staphyloma.
Scleral staphyloma is a type of scleral disease and it is exactly synonymous with Scleral ectasia.

Frey syndrome is a type of autonomic nervous system disease that is characterized by facial sweating and flushing with gustatory stimulation, resulting from a disruption of the auriculotemporal nerve pathways. It is also known by exact synonyms such as Baillarger syndrome, gustatory hyperhidrosis, and gustatory sweating.

Pericardium cancer is identified as something that intersects with cancer and a disease, specifically located in the pericardium. It is considered a type of pericardium disease and also categorized under heart cancer. Moreover, pericardium cancer is exactly synonymous with Pericardial tumor, malignant neoplasm of pericardium, and malignant tumor of Pericardium.

Infant gynecomastia is a type of breast disease and is defined as a breast disease characterized by the benign proliferation of glandular breast tissue, occurring in children less than one year of age. It has exact synonyms, including Neonatal gynaecomastia and breast engorgement in newborn.

Fungal meningitis is a type of meningitis and a specific form of fungal infectious disease that at least has a material basis in some fungi. It is defined as a meningitis that has its material basis in a fungal infection.

Polycystic ovary syndrome is a type of ovarian dysfunction characterized by hyperandrogenism, polycystic ovaries, hirsutism, oligomenorrhea or amenorrhea, anovulation, and excessive body weight. It has several exact synonyms, including Multicystic ovaries, PCOS, Polycystic Ovarian disease, Polycystic ovaries, Stein-Leventhal synd., and Stein-Leventhal syndrome, as well as polycystic ovary.
Hyperandrogenism, which is a type of disorder of sexual development, is also exactly known as hyperandrogenization syndrome.

Penile cancer is identical to an intersection of something that is cancer and something that, at minimum, is a disease located in the penis. It is a type of penile disease as well as a type of cancer affecting the male reproductive organ. Penile cancer is exactly synonymous with several terms, including Ca penis, Penile Ca, malignant Penile tumor, malignant neoplasm of the body of the penis, and penile neoplasm.
Dental pulp necrosis is a type of dental pulp disease characterized by the death of the pulp tissue. It is also exactly synonymous with necrosis of the pulp, necrotic pulp, and pulp necrosis.

Penile benign neoplasm is identical to an intersection of benign neoplasm and diseases located in the penis. It is a type of male reproductive organ benign neoplasm and also classified as a type of penile disease. Furthermore, penile benign neoplasm is exactly synonymous with "Penile tumor" and "neoplasm of penis."

Pelvic muscle wasting, which is a type of prolapse of the female genital organ, is defined as a condition characterized by a decrease in muscle mass and tissue in the pelvic floor, vagina, vulva, and urinary tract. This condition can occur due to aging, menopause, and the subsequent reduction of estrogen, or a combination of these factors.

Thyroid hormone resistance syndrome is a type of hypothyroidism and is exactly synonymous with Generalized thyroid hormone resistance, Refetoff syndrome, Thyroid hormone responsiveness defect, and thyroid hormone resistance.

fragment:

:myxedema rdfs:subClassOf :hypothyroidism .
text: myxedema is a type of hypothyroidism.
Accommodative spasm, which has the exact synonym "Spasm of Accommodation," is a type of eye accommodation disease.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:presbyopia rdfs:subClassOf :eye_accommodation_disease .
text: presbyopia is a type of eye accommodation disease.

Bronchopulmonary dysplasia is a type of lung disease and also a condition that starts during neonatal onset. It is defined as a lung disease characterized by underdeveloped lungs in newborns that can be easily irritated or inflamed after birth, leading to damage to the alveoli of the lungs and bronchi. Most newborns who develop bronchopulmonary dysplasia are born more than 10 weeks before their due dates, weigh less than 2 pounds at birth, and have breathing problems. It is also known by exact synonyms including Bronchopulmonary dysplasia of newborn, Chronic lung disease of prematurity, Neonatal chronic lung disease, Perinatal bronchopulmonary dysplasia, Respiratory insufficiency, and Neonatal chronic respiratory disease.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:conjunctival_deposit rdfs:subClassOf :conjunctival_disease .
text: conjunctival deposit is a type of conjunctival disease.

Cicatricial pemphigoid is a type of pemphigoid that is characterized by skin lesions and scarring, primarily located in mucous membranes and skin. It is also known by several exact synonyms, including Cicatricial pemphigoid with ocular involvement, Ocular pemphigoid, Benign mucous membrane pemphigoid, Benign mucous membrane pemphigoid with ocular involvement, and Ocular pemphigus.

Palindromic rheumatism is a type of arthritis and something that at least has arthritis as a symptom. It is defined as an arthritis that involves sudden and rapidly developing attacks of arthritis with a remission period that results in no joint damage or symptoms. Moreover, palindromic rheumatism has exact synonyms, including Hench's syndrome and Hench-Rosenberg syndrome.

Blue color blindness, also known by its exact synonyms Tritan defect and Tritanopia, is a type of color blindness and a specific form of autosomal dominant disease. It is characterized by a selective deficiency of blue vision, which has its material basis in autosomal dominant inheritance, particularly due to a mutation in the OPN1SW gene. This condition is associated with a deficiency or absence of blue-sensitive cone photoreceptor function. Additionally, blue color blindness is recognized as a condition that inherently has a material basis in some form of autosomal dominant inheritance.
Nephrosclerosis is a type of renal hypertension and has the exact synonym "renal sclerosis."
Patau syndrome is a type of chromosomal disease, which is exactly synonymous with D1 Trisomy and trisomy 13. Additionally, it is relatedly known as Patau's syndrome.

Hypopigmentation of the eyelid is a type of pigmentation disease, eyelid disease, and is something that at least one disease has located on the eyelid. It is defined as a pigmentation disease characterized by the loss of pigmentation on the eyelid, with symptoms including white or light macules or patches on the eyelid. The condition may have a material basis in autoimmune conditions like vitiligo, chronic inflammation, malignancy, or exposure to destructive substances.
Hypertrichosis of the eyelid is a type of hypertrichosis and also a type of eyelid disease. It is categorized under conditions that have the eyelid as their location.
Hypotrichosis of the eyelid is a type of hypotrichosis and a type of eyelid disease, indicating it is a condition that affects the eyelids and involves a lesser amount of hair than normal.

Onchocerciasis is a type of filariasis and is also recognized by exact synonyms such as infection by Onchocerca volvulus, Onchocerca volvulus infection, and volvulosis. It is characterized by a parasitic infection caused by the nematode Onchocerca volvulus, which humans contract through the bite of a blackfly of the genus Simulium. The disease's material basis is in Onchocerca volvulus, and it features several symptoms including blindness, eczema, itching, enlargement of lymph nodes, and lymphadenopathy. Additionally, onchocerciasis is associated with dermatitis as a significant disease feature. When the worms die, they cause intense itching and provoke a strong immune system response that can destroy adjacent tissue, leading to pruritus, dermatitis, blindness, onchocercomata (subcutaneous nodules), and lymphadenopathy.

Familial hyperlipidemia is a type of lipid metabolism disorder and has exact synonyms including familial hyperlipoproteinemia and hyperlipemia. Additionally, it has a related synonym, hyperlipidaemia.

@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:melanoacanthoma rdfs:subClassOf :seborrheic_keratosis .
text: melanoacanthoma is a type of seborrheic keratosis.

@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:inflamed_seborrheic_keratosis rdfs:subClassOf :seborrheic_keratosis .
text: inflamed seborrheic keratosis is a type of seborrheic keratosis.
Acute apical periodontitis is a type of periapical periodontitis and it has an exact synonym, which is acute apical periodontitis of pulpal origin.

Portal vein thrombosis is a type of thrombosis, vein disease, and hepatic vascular disease. It is equivalent to an intersection of something that is both a thrombosis and a disease located in the portal vein. Furthermore, it is also a type of condition where the disease is located in a vein. Portal vein thrombosis is defined as a hepatic vascular disease characterized by a blood clot that forms within the hepatic portal vein.

Heart cancer is the same as something that intersects with something that is cancer and something that is at least a disease located in the heart. It is a type of heart disease as well as a type of cardiovascular cancer. Heart cancer is defined as a cardiovascular cancer located in the heart. Additionally, heart cancer has exact synonyms including Cardiac tumor, Tumour of heart, malignant Cardiac tumor, and malignant neoplasm of heart.

Selective IgA deficiency disease is a type of dysgammaglobulinemia defined as a selective immunoglobulin deficiency disease stemming from a deficiency of immunoglobulin A (IgA). This antibody plays a crucial role in protecting against infections of the mucous membranes lining the mouth, airways, and digestive tract. It is also known by exact synonyms such as Immunoglobulin A deficiency, Selective immunoglobulin A deficiency, and selective IgA immunodeficiency.

Dysgammaglobulinemia is a type of selective immunoglobulin deficiency disease which is defined as a selective immunoglobulin deficiency that is caused by a reduction in some types of gamma globulins. Additionally, it has an exact match in the Medical Subject Headings (MESH) with the identifier D004406.

Hyperlipoproteinemia type V is a type of familial hyperlipidemia and it is also known by several exact synonyms including Fredrickson type V lipaemia, familial hyperlipoproteinemia type V, and familial type 5 hyperlipoproteinemia.

Lipoatrophic diabetes mellitus is a type of type 2 diabetes mellitus that is defined as a type 2 diabetes mellitus characterized by severe insulin resistance and lipodystrophy. It is also exactly synonymous with lipoatrophic diabetes.

Diabetic angiopathy is a type of peripheral vascular disease, which is defined as a peripheral vascular disease characterized by the narrowing of the arteries as a complication arising from chronic diabetes. Furthermore, it is exactly synonymous with Diabetic vascular disorder and diabetic peripheral angiopathy.
Gestational diabetes is a type of diabetes mellitus that manifests during pregnancy. It has exact synonyms such as GDM, Gestational diabetes mellitus, and Maternal gestational diabetes mellitus.

Prediabetes syndrome is a type of glucose metabolism disease characterized by blood glucose levels that are high but not high enough to be classified as type 2 diabetes. It has exact synonyms including Prediabetes, impaired glucose tolerance, and prediabetic state.

Neonatal diabetes is a type of diabetes mellitus and is also a type of condition that begins in infancy. It is defined as a diabetes mellitus that is characterized by hyperglycemia occurring within the first 6 months of life. Furthermore, it has the exact synonyms "diabetes mellitus syndrome in newborn infant" and "neonatal diabetes mellitus."
Antidepressant type abuse is a form of substance abuse that is characterized by the recurring use of antidepressant drugs despite negative consequences.
Oculopharyngeal muscular dystrophy is a type of muscular dystrophy, which is exactly synonymous with Muscular dystrophy, oculopharyngeal.

        "Fredrickson type IV Lipidemia"@en,
        "Fredrickson type IV hyperlipoproteinemia"@en,
        "Fredrickson type IV lipidaemia"@en,
        "VLDL hyperlipoproteinemia"@en,
        "familial hypertriglyceridemia"@en .
text: Hyperlipoproteinemia type IV is a type of familial hyperlipidemia and is exactly synonymous with Endogenous hyperlipidaemia, Fredrickson type IV Lipidemia, Fredrickson type IV hyperlipoproteinemia, Fredrickson type IV lipidaemia, VLDL hyperlipoproteinemia, and familial hypertriglyceridemia.

Distal myopathy, which is a type of muscular dystrophy and also known as Miyoshi muscular dystrophy or distal muscular dystrophy, is characterized by predominant weakness and atrophy beginning in the feet and/or hands. This condition is a type of something that at least has the symptom of muscle weakness.

Glycogen storage disease VII is a type of autosomal recessive disease and is a specific form of glycogen storage disease. It is characterized by a condition that at least has its material basis in autosomal recessive inheritance. Specifically, this disease is described as a glycogen storage disease that manifests through symptoms such as exercise intolerance, muscle cramping, exertional myopathy, and compensated hemolysis. These symptoms have their material basis in either homozygous or compound heterozygous mutations in the PFKM gene, which is responsible for encoding muscle phosphofructokinase and is located on chromosome 12q13. Furthermore, glycogen storage disease VII is also known by several exact synonyms: Glycogen storage disease 7, Glycogen storage disease, type VII, Muscle phosphofructokinase deficiency, glycogen storage disease type VII, and phosphofructokinase myopathy.

Myotonic Dystrophy Type 1 is a specific kind of myotonic disease that is characterized by its relation to a certain trinucleotide repeat expansion in its material basis. It is also defined by symptoms such as muscle weakness. Specifically, it is described as a myotonic disease that manifests through progressive muscle wasting and weakness, particularly affecting the distal skeletal and smooth muscles of the lower legs, hands, neck, and face. Additionally, it involves myotonia and cataracts, with its material basis being the autosomal dominant inheritance of the DMPK gene, which contains an expansion of a CTG trinucleotide repeat in the non-coding region. Myotonic Dystrophy Type 1 is also known by several exact synonyms, including Dystrophia Myotonica, Steinert Disease, Congenital Myotonic Dystrophy, and Myotonic Dystrophy of Steinert.

Duchenne muscular dystrophy is a type of muscular dystrophy and an X-linked recessive disease. It is characterized by a material basis in some X-linked recessive inheritance and presents symptoms such as muscle weakness and progressive weakness. Duchenne muscular dystrophy is defined as a muscular dystrophy that has its material basis in X-linked mutations in the DMD gene located on the X chromosome. This condition is marked by rapidly progressing muscle weakness and muscle atrophy, initially affecting the lower extremities and eventually the whole body. It primarily affects males, while females can be carriers. The symptoms typically begin before the age of six and may appear in infancy. Additionally, it has an exact synonym, which is Muscular dystrophy, Duchenne.

Limb girdle muscular dystrophy is a type of muscular dystrophy characterized by the weakening of the muscles of the hip and shoulders, which comprise the limb girdle muscles. It is also exactly synonymous with Erb's muscular dystrophy, Leyden-Mbius muscular dystrophy, and is referred to by its own name, limb girdle muscular dystrophy.

Cornelia de Lange Syndrome is a type of syndrome that is a monogenic disease, meaning it has a basis in some gene. It is defined as a syndrome characterized by slow growth before and after birth, intellectual disability that is usually severe to profound, skeletal abnormalities involving the arms and hands, and distinctive facial features. Additionally, Cornelia de Lange Syndrome is also known by the exact synonyms Brachmann de Lange Syndrome and De Lange Syndrome.

Emery Dreifuss muscular dystrophy is a type of muscular dystrophy that has the exact synonym EDMD. It is defined as a muscular dystrophy that chiefly affects muscles used for movement (skeletal) and heart (cardiac) muscle.

Facioscapulohumeral muscular dystrophy is a type of muscular dystrophy and has exact synonyms including Landouzy Dejerine muscular dystrophy, Landouzy-Dejerine muscular dystrophy, and Muscular dystrophy, Landouzy-Dejerine.

Lyme disease is a primary bacterial infectious disease with a material basis in Borrelia burgdorferi. It is transmitted by ticks, specifically through tick-borne transmission involving the blacklegged tick (Ixodes scapularis) and the western blacklegged tick (Ixodes pacificus), either individually or through a union of both. The symptoms of Lyme disease include fever, headache, and fatigue. Additionally, if left untreated, the infection may spread to joints, the heart, and the nervous system, and it may present a skin rash called erythema migrans. Lyme disease is also known by several exact synonyms, including Bannwarth syndrome, Bannworth's syndrome, Lyme borreliosis, Neurological Lyme disease, Lyme neuroborreliosis, and neuroborreliosis.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:odontoclasia rdfs:subClassOf :dental_caries .
text: odontoclasia is a type of dental caries.

A parametrium malignant neoplasm is equivalent to an entity that is both a cancer and a disease located in the parametrium. It is a type of uterine adnexa cancer. Furthermore, a parametrium malignant neoplasm is defined as a uterine adnexa cancer located in the parametrium.
Uterine adnexa cancer, a type of uterine cancer, is defined as a uterine cancer that is located in the adnexa.

Round ligament malignant neoplasm is defined as a uterine adnexa cancer that is located in the round ligament, equivalent to the intersection of cancer and diseases located in some part of the round ligament of the uterus. It is a specific type of uterine adnexa cancer. Moreover, round ligament malignant neoplasm is exactly synonymous with both malignant neoplasm of the round ligament and malignant neoplasm of the round ligament of the uterus.

Bordetella parapertussis whooping cough is a type of pertussis and is defined as a milder disease caused by the bacterium Bordetella parapertussis. This disease has symptoms including coughing, sneezing, and a runny nose, which is also known as rhinorrhea. Additionally, Bordetella parapertussis whooping cough is characterized by at least having symptoms such as sneezing, rhinorrhea, and cough.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:acute_endophthalmitis rdfs:subClassOf :purulent_endophthalmitis .
text: acute endophthalmitis is a type of purulent endophthalmitis.
Siderosis of the eye is a type of eye degenerative disease characterized by intraocular iron toxicity, typically due to a retained foreign body. It is also known as Siderosis of the globe.
Choledocholithiasis is a type of common bile duct disease characterized by the presence of at least one gallstone in the common bile duct.

Iron deficiency anemia is a type of nutritional deficiency disease characterized by pallor, fatigue, lightheadedness, and weakness. It has a material basis in low total body iron, causing impaired synthesis of red blood cells.
Hypochromic anemia is a type of anemia and it is exactly synonymous with ANEMIA HYPOCHROMIC.

Bronchial disease is equivalent to a condition that is both a disease and specifically located in either the bronchus or the bronchiole. Additionally, bronchial disease falls under the category of lower respiratory tract disease. It is defined as a lower respiratory tract disease that impacts the airways leading into the lungs, which may arise from inflammation of the bronchi and bronchioles, infection, or blockage.

Kohler's disease is a type of osteochondrosis, which is defined as an osteochondrosis that results in death and collapse located in the navicular bone of the foot. It is also exactly synonymous with Juvenile osteochondrosis of the foot and Kohler disease.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:blind_hypotensive_eye rdfs:subClassOf :ocular_hypotension .
text: blind hypotensive eye is a type of ocular hypotension.
Spontaneous ocular nystagmus is a type of pathologic nystagmus and has exact synonyms such as Ocular nystagmus, Searching eye movements, and visual deprivation nystagmus.
Leukocoria is a type of eye degenerative disease and it has an exact synonym, Leucocoria.

Absolute glaucoma is a type of glaucoma characterized by a total loss of vision, uncontrolled pressure in the eye, severe pain in the eye, absence of pupillary light reflex, absence of pupillary response, and the eye having a stony appearance. It is also exactly synonymous with "blind hypertensive eye."

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:regular_astigmatism rdfs:subClassOf :astigmatism .
text: regular astigmatism is a type of astigmatism.

Astigmatism is a type of refractive error, which is defined as a refractive error characterized by the inability of the optics of the eye to focus a point object into a sharp focused image on the retina. Additionally, it has a symptom of blurred vision.
Necrosis of the ear ossicle is a type of auditory system disease and has the exact synonym "partial loss or necrosis of ear ossicles."

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:splenic_sequestration rdfs:subClassOf :splenic_disease .
text: splenic sequestration is a type of splenic disease.

fragment:
