:chronic_congestive_splenomegaly rdfs:subClassOf :splenic_disease .
text: chronic congestive splenomegaly is a type of splenic disease.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:phthisical_cornea rdfs:subClassOf :corneal_degeneration .
text: phthisical cornea is a type of corneal degeneration.

Chronic laryngitis is a type of laryngitis defined as a condition where symptoms persist for more than three weeks. Factors such as gastroesophageal reflux and lingering bronchitis can cause this disease.
Pericardial effusion, a type of pericardium disease, is defined as a condition characterized by an abnormal accumulation of fluid in the pericardial cavity.

Protein energy malnutrition is a type of nutritional deficiency disease characterized by inadequate dietary protein and calories. This condition can lead to profound systemic effects, including decreased metabolism, altered tissue distribution, compromised immunity, and impaired growth. The material basis of protein energy malnutrition lies in dietary deprivation.

Bladder neck cancer is the same as something that is an intersection of something that is cancer and something that is at least a disease located in the neck of the urinary bladder. It is a type of urinary bladder cancer. Additionally, bladder neck cancer has exact synonyms which include malignant neoplasm of the urinary bladder neck and malignant tumor of the bladder neck.
Urinary bladder posterior wall cancer, which is a type of urinary bladder cancer, has an exact synonym: malignant neoplasm of the posterior wall of the urinary bladder.

Bladder sarcoma is a type of urinary bladder cancer and a kind of sarcoma. It is identified as a cancer that intersects with conditions deriving at least from some embryonic cell metazoa and is a disease that is located in the urinary bladder. Bladder sarcoma is defined as a sarcoma and malignant neoplasm of the urinary bladder that is located in the bladder. Additionally, bladder sarcoma is exactly synonymous with both sarcoma of the bladder and sarcoma of the urinary bladder.

Bladder trigone cancer is the same as the intersection of cancer and a disease that has its location in the trigone of the urinary bladder. It is a type of urinary bladder cancer. Moreover, bladder trigone cancer has exact synonyms including malignant neoplasm of the trigone of the urinary bladder, malignant tumor of the trigone of the bladder, and malignant tumor of the trigone of the urinary bladder.
Urinary bladder anterior wall cancer, which is a type of urinary bladder cancer, is exactly synonymous with malignant neoplasm of the anterior wall of the urinary bladder.
Vitreous syneresis is a type of vitreous disease and is exactly synonymous with vitreous degeneration.

Urachus cancer, which is the same as an entity that intersects the categories of cancer and diseases located in the urachus, is a type of urinary bladder cancer. Additionally, urachus cancer is exactly synonymous with a malignant tumor of the urachus.

Ureteric orifice cancer is the same as something that is both a cancer and a disease located at the ureteral orifice. It is a type of urinary bladder cancer and has exact synonyms including "Orifice of the Ureter," "malignant neoplasm of ureteric orifice of urinary bladder," and "malignant tumor of ureteric orifice."

Ureter cancer is identical to an entity that is both a cancer and a disease, which has its location in the ureter. It is classified as a type of ureteral disease as well as a type of urinary system cancer. The definition of ureter cancer is a urinary system cancer that is located in the ureter. Furthermore, ureter cancer is exactly synonymous with malignant tumor of the ureter and malignant ureteral tumor.

Bladder dome cancer is a type of urinary bladder cancer and it has several exact synonyms. These include Superior Surface of bladder, malignant neoplasm of apex of urinary bladder, malignant neoplasm of dome of urinary bladder, and malignant tumor of vault of bladder.
Bladder lymphoma is a type of lymphoma and a type of urinary bladder cancer, which at least has a material basis in some lymphocyte. It has the exact synonym "Lymphoma of the urinary bladder."
Hepatorenal syndrome is a type of acute kidney failure and is defined as an acute kidney failure characterized by severe renal vasoconstriction.

Multicentric reticulohistiocytosis is a type of syndrome characterized by papulonodular skin lesions containing a proliferation of true macrophages associated with arthritis. It is also exactly synonymous with Lipoid dermatoarthritis.

Degenerative myopia is a type of myopia, which is exactly synonymous with degenerative progressive high myopia, pathological myopia, progressive high (degenerative) myopia, and progressive high myopia.

Myopia is a type of refractive error and is defined as a refractive error characterized by the inability to see farther objects clearly. It has exact synonyms such as near vision, near-sightedness, and short-sightedness. Furthermore, myopia has an exact match with MESH:D009216.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:cortical_blindness rdfs:subClassOf :visual_cortex_disease .
text: cortical blindness is a type of visual cortex disease.
Visual epilepsy is a type of epilepsy and it is exactly synonymous with the term epilepsy, visual.

Clubfoot is a type of bone development disease that occurs in the foot. It is defined as a bone development disease where one or both feet are inclined inwards, axially rotated outwards, and pointing downwards, accompanied by concomitant soft tissue abnormalities. Clubfoot has exact synonyms, including Congenital equinovarus, Equinovarus deformity of foot, congenital clubfoot, and congenital talipes equinovarus.

Penis sarcoma is a type of sarcoma and also a type of penile cancer that derives from some embryonic cell metazoa. It is defined as a sarcoma and malignant neoplasm of the penis that is located in the penis. Moreover, it has the exact synonym "sarcoma of penis."

Glans penis cancer is the same as something that is both a cancer and a disease with a location in the glans penis. It is a type of penile cancer. This condition is also exactly synonymous with malignant neoplasm of glans penis, malignant tumor of glans penis, and malignant tumour of glans penis.

Nephrotic syndrome is a type of nephrosis that is defined by a nephrosis characterized by a marked increase in glomerular protein permeability. This results in a marked elevation of urine protein levels, hypoalbuminemia, hyperlipidemia, and hypercoagulability.
Coronary artery vasospasm is a type of coronary artery disease and has exact synonyms such as Coronary Vasospasm and Coronary artery spasm.

Coronary artery anomaly is a type of coronary artery disease and it has exact synonyms including Congenital anomaly of coronary artery, Coronary artery abnormality, and Coronary artery anomaly, congenital.

Coronary thrombosis is a type of thrombosis and also a type of coronary artery disease, which is synonymous with Coronary artery thrombosis. It is defined as an intersection of conditions that are thrombosis and diseases located in the coronary artery.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:transient_refractive_change rdfs:subClassOf :refractive_error .
text: transient refractive change is a type of refractive error.

Indeterminate leprosy is a type of leprosy and also a type of something that is at least transmitted by droplet spread transmission. It is defined as an early form of the disease that causes one to a few hypopigmented or erythematous macules. Additionally, indeterminate leprosy is exactly synonymous with uncharacteristic leprosy.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:monocular_exotropia rdfs:subClassOf :exotropia .
text: monocular exotropia is a type of exotropia.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:peripheral_focal_chorioretinitis rdfs:subClassOf :focal_chorioretinitis .
text: peripheral focal chorioretinitis is a type of focal chorioretinitis.
Tibial neuropathy, which is a type of mononeuropathy, has the exact synonym "Posterior tibial neuropathy."

Pick's disease is a type of frontotemporal dementia characterized by a spectrum of neuropsychiatric symptoms that range from those affecting the patient's personality to those causing a decline in cognitive function. It is also known by exact synonyms such as Dementia in Pick's disease, LOBAR ATROPHY OF BRAIN, PICK DISEASE OF BRAIN, and Pick disease. Moreover, Pick's disease has an exact match with the identifier MESH:D020774.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:macular_keratitis rdfs:subClassOf :keratitis .
text: macular keratitis is a type of keratitis.
An abnormal threshold of rods, which has an exact synonym as an abnormal dark adaptation curve, is a type of night blindness.
Denture stomatitis is a type of stomatitis and it is exactly synonymous with Denture sore mouth.
Mononeuropathy is a type of neuropathy that is defined as a neuropathy characterized by damage to a single nerve, resulting in the loss of movement, sensation, or other function of that nerve.

Ureteral benign neoplasm, which is the same as something that intersects with something that is a benign neoplasm and something that is at least a disease located in the ureter, is a type of ureteral disease and also a type of urinary system benign neoplasm. Furthermore, it has exact synonyms including neoplasm of ureter and ureteral tumor.

Ureter leiomyoma is a type of ureteral benign neoplasm, a type of leiomyoma, and a type of entity that at least derives from some smooth muscle cell. It is defined as an ureteral benign neoplasm that derives from smooth muscle cells. Furthermore, ureter leiomyoma has an exact synonym: ureteral leiomyoma.

Schwannoma of the ureter is the same as something that intersects neurilemmoma and a disease that has its location in the ureter. This condition is a type of ureteral benign neoplasm and also a type of peripheral nerve schwannoma. Additionally, Schwannoma of the ureter is exactly synonymous with ureteral schwannoma.

Female breast nipple and areola cancer is a type of female breast cancer that is defined as a female breast cancer located in the nipple and areola. It has exact synonyms, including malignant neoplasm of nipple and areola of female breast, and malignant neoplasm of nipple or areola of female breast.

Vaginal cancer, which is a type of female reproductive organ cancer and also falls under the category of vaginal diseases, is defined as a female reproductive system cancer located in the vagina. This condition is equivalent to a cancer that intersects with a disease located in the vagina. Vaginal cancer is known by several exact synonyms, including malignant neoplasm of vagina, malignant tumor of vagina, malignant vaginal tumor, neoplasm of vagina, vagina neoplasm, and vaginal tumor.

Labium majus cancer is a type of vulva cancer that is specifically located in the labium majus. It is defined as a vulva cancer situated in the labium majus. Moreover, this condition has exact synonyms, including malignant neoplasm of labia majora and malignant tumor of Labia Majora.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:ecthyma rdfs:subClassOf :impetigo .
text: ecthyma is a type of impetigo.
Gastroparesis is a type of functional gastric disease and has exact synonyms such as Gastroparalysis, Gastroparesis syndrome, and gastric atonia.

Tinea cruris is a type of dermatophytosis, also known exactly as Dermatophytosis of groin & perianal area, Dhobie itch, or dermatophytosis of groin and perianal area. It is a disease that specifically affects locations including the perineum, the inguinal part of the abdomen, and the perianal skin. Tinea cruris is defined as a dermatophytosis that results in a fungal skin infection located in the groin, perineum, or perianal region. This infection is caused by Ascomycota fungi that belong to a group called dermatophytes. It is characterized by symptoms such as itching in the groin, thigh skin folds, or anus and leads to the formation of a rash. This rash appears as raised red plaques (platelike areas) and scaly patches with sharply defined borders that may blister and ooze.

Peripheral nervous system neoplasm is defined as a nervous system cancer that is situated in the peripheral nervous system. This condition is identified as the same as an entity that is both a type of cancer and a disease located specifically in the peripheral nervous system. Furthermore, peripheral nervous system neoplasm falls under the categories of both nervous system cancer and peripheral nervous system disease. It is also exactly synonymous with neoplasm of peripheral nerve, nerve sheath neoplasm, and tumor of PNS.

Tracheal cancer is equivalent to a condition that is both a type of cancer and a disease with its location in the trachea. It is classified as a type of respiratory system cancer as well as a type of tracheal disease. Additionally, tracheal cancer is defined as a respiratory system cancer located in the trachea.

Head and neck cancer is identical to a condition that is an intersection of cancer and a disease located in an area that encompasses both the head and neck. It is classified as a type of organ system cancer. This cancer originates in the head or neck region, which includes the nasal cavity, sinuses, lips, mouth, salivary glands, throat, or larynx. Additionally, head and neck cancer is precisely synonymous with the terms head and neck neoplasm, head and neck tumours, head/neck neoplasm, and tumor of head and neck.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:creutzfeldt_jakob_disease rdfs:subClassOf :prion_disease ;
    :has_exact_synonym "CJD"@en,
        "Creutzfeldt Jacob syndrome"@en,
        "Creutzfeldt Jakob disease"@en,
        "Creutzfeldt-Jacob disease"@en,
        "Jakob-Creutzfeldt disease"@en,
        "Subacute spongiform encephalopathy"@en,
        "Transmissible virus dementia"@en .
text: Creutzfeldt Jakob Disease (CJD) is a type of prion disease that goes by several exact synonyms, including Creutzfeldt Jacob Syndrome, Creutzfeldt Jakob Disease, Creutzfeldt-Jacob Disease, Jakob-Creutzfeldt Disease, Subacute Spongiform Encephalopathy, and Transmissible Virus Dementia.
Ischemic neuropathy is a type of neuropathy and it has an exact synonym, Ischemic peripheral neuropathy.
Esophagitis is a type of esophageal disease and it is exactly synonymous with acute esophagitis.

Postmenopausal atrophic vaginitis is a type of vaginitis and has the definition of a vaginitis that occurs in postmenopausal women, characterized by vaginal atrophy secondary to estrogen deficiency. It has exact synonyms, including Senile vaginitis and atrophic vaginitis.
Synostosis is a type of dysostosis characterized by the abnormal fusing of adjacent bones.
Coloboma of the optic nerve is a type of visual pathway disease and has exact synonyms including "Coloboma of optic disc" and "Morning glory syndrome".

Botulism is a primary bacterial infectious disease that is a type of intoxication caused by botulinum neurotoxins (BoNTA, B, E, and F), which are located in the neuromuscular junction resulting in descending muscle paralysis. This disease has a material basis in various strains of Clostridium botulinum, specifically Clostridium botulinum A, Clostridium botulinum B, Clostridium botulinum E, and Clostridium botulinum F. Botulism is also known by several exact synonyms, including Botulism poisoning, Food poisoning due to Clostridium botulinum, Foodborne botulism, Infection due to Clostridium botulinum, and Intoxication with Clostridium botulinum toxin.
Morbid obesity is a type of obesity and it is also exactly synonymous with severe obesity.

Prader Willi Syndrome is a type of syndrome which is also classified as a chromosomal disease. It is characterized by weak muscle tone, feeding difficulties, poor growth, and delayed development. Starting from childhood, individuals affected by this syndrome develop an insatiable appetite, leading to chronic overeating and obesity. The basis of Prader Willi Syndrome is linked to at least one symptom, and it has a material basis in a complex genetic situation involving a union of maternal uniparental disomy, loss of function variant, paternal variant, chromosomal deletion, and chromosomal translocation. It is also known by its exact synonym, Prader Willi Syndrome.

Hypertrophic cardiomyopathy is a type of intrinsic cardiomyopathy, which is defined as an intrinsic cardiomyopathy characterized by abnormal thickening (hypertrophy) of the heart without any obvious cause. It is also exactly synonymous with hypertrophic obstructive cardiomyopathy.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:conjunctival_concretion rdfs:subClassOf :conjunctival_deposit .
text: conjunctival concretion is a type of conjunctival deposit.
Ulceroglandular tularemia is a type of tularemia defined by a tularemia that results in painful regional lymphadenopathy and an ulcerated skin lesion.

Osteopoikilosis is a type of osteosclerosis and is also a type of condition that at least has a phenotype characterized by increased bone mineral density. It is defined as an osteosclerosis that results in numerous bone islands located within the skeleton.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:atrophy_of_testis rdfs:subClassOf :testicular_disease .
text: atrophy of testis is a type of testicular disease.
Spermatic cord torsion is a type of testicular disease, which is also exactly known as Torsion of testicle, Torsion of testis, and testicular Torsion.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:spermatocele rdfs:subClassOf :male_reproductive_system_disease .
text: spermatocele is a type of male reproductive system disease.

Female reproductive organ cancer is identified as a cancer that intersects with a disease located in the female reproductive system, which includes organs such as the ovaries, fallopian tubes, uterus, cervix, vagina, and vulva. This type of cancer is a subtype of both reproductive organ cancer and female reproductive system disease. It is defined specifically as a reproductive organ cancer manifested in the female genitals. Furthermore, female reproductive organ cancer is exactly synonymous with female reproductive cancer, malignant gynecologic tumor, and malignant neoplasm of female genital organ.

Tracheal lymphoma is a type of lymphoma and a type of tracheal cancer. It is a condition that has a material basis in some lymphocyte. Furthermore, it is exactly synonymous with both Lymphoma of Trachea and lymphoma of the trachea.

Trachea sarcoma is a type of sarcoma and also a type of tracheal cancer. It is a disease that originates from certain embryonic cell metazoa, and its location is specifically in the trachea. Defined as a sarcoma and malignant tumor located in the trachea, it is exactly synonymous with sarcoma of the trachea.

Trachea squamous cell carcinoma is a type of squamous cell carcinoma, a type of trachea carcinoma, and a type of something that at least derives from some squamous epithelial cell. It is defined as a squamous cell carcinoma that is located in the trachea and has the exact synonym Tracheal Epidermoid carcinoma.
Trigeminal nerve neoplasm is a type of cranial nerve malignant neoplasm, and it has exact synonyms such as neoplasm of trigeminal nerve and tumor of Trigeminal nerve.
Anterior ischemic optic neuropathy is a type of optic nerve disease and is exactly synonymous with ischemic optic neuropathy.

Frontal lobe neoplasm is equivalent to an entity that is both a cancer and a disease located in the frontal lobe. It is a specific type of cerebrum cancer. Furthermore, frontal lobe neoplasm is precisely synonymous with malignant neoplasm of frontal lobe, neoplasm of frontal lobe, and tumor of frontal lobe.
Conn's syndrome is a type of adrenal adenoma characterized by the overproduction of aldosterone. It is also precisely known as Conn syndrome, primary aldosteronism, and primary hyperaldosteronism.

Sympathetic ophthalmia is a type of panuveitis and also falls under the category of conditions that have symptoms like pain and photophobia. It is defined as a panuveitis characterized by bilateral diffuse intraocular inflammation following penetrating trauma to an eye, and it exhibits symptoms such as blurry vision, watering, pain, and photophobia. Furthermore, sympathetic ophthalmia is exactly synonymous with sympathetic uveitis.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:drug_induced_mental_disorder rdfs:subClassOf :substance_induced_psychosis .
text: drug induced mental disorder is a type of substance induced psychosis.

Panuveitis is a type of uveitis and also a type of condition that at least has the symptom of some inflammation. It is defined as an uveitis characterized by inflammation of all layers of the uvea (middle layer) of the eye, which includes the iris, ciliary body, and choroid. Furthermore, panuveitis has an exact synonym, which is Diffuse uveitis.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:kernicterus_due_to_isoimmunization rdfs:subClassOf :neonatal_jaundice .
text: kernicterus due to isoimmunization is a type of neonatal jaundice.

Allergic disease, which is synonymous with allergic hypersensitivity disease, hypersensitivity, and hypersensitivity reaction type I disease, is characterized as an immune system disease that represents an exaggerated immune response to allergens such as insect venom, dust mites, pollen, pet dander, drugs, or some foods. This condition is defined by a specific reaction where the disease intersects with conditions that at least manifest some allergic reaction symptoms. Additionally, allergic disease falls under the category of immune system diseases and is identified with the OBI code 9991118.

Cryptococcosis is a type of opportunistic mycosis and is defined as an opportunistic mycosis that results in a fungal infection with a material basis in Cryptococcus neoformans or Cryptococcus gattii. It has exact synonyms including Busse-Buschke's disease, European cryptococcosis, cryptococcal infection, torula, and torulosis. Additionally, cryptococcosis has a related synonym, Cryptococcus neoformans infection, and an exact match in the Medical Subject Headings (MESH) with the identifier D003453.
Sarcoid meningitis, which is a type of neurosarcoidosis, has the exact synonym "Meningitis in sarcoidosis."

Rett syndrome is classified as a type of pervasive developmental disorder, which is defined as a pervasive developmental disease characterized by normal early growth and development, followed by a slowing of development, loss of purposeful use of the hands, distinctive hand movements, slowed brain and head growth, problems with walking, seizures, and intellectual disability. Furthermore, Rett syndrome is also precisely known as Rett's disorder and cerebroatrophic hyperammonemia.

Mediastinum neurofibroma is identified as an entity that intersects with neurofibroma and a disease that is located specifically in the mediastinum. It is classified as a type of neurofibroma and also as a type of malignant mediastinal neurogenic neoplasm. Furthermore, mediastinum neurofibroma is exactly synonymous with Neurofibroma of mediastinum.
Dieulafoy lesion is a type of stomach disease that is also exactly synonymous with Dieulafoy lesion (hemorrhagic) of the intestine and dieulafoy lesion (hemorrhagic) of the stomach and duodenum.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:pylorospasm rdfs:subClassOf :stomach_disease .
text: pylorospasm is a type of stomach disease.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:transient_arthropathy rdfs:subClassOf :transient_arthritis ;
    :has_exact_synonym "Transient arthropathy involving forearm"@en,
        "Transient arthropathy involving hand"@en,
        "Transient arthropathy involving lower leg"@en,
        "Transient arthropathy involving multiple sites"@en,
        "Transient arthropathy involving pelvic region and thigh"@en,
        "Transient arthropathy involving shoulder region"@en,
        "Transient arthropathy involving upper arm"@en .
text: Transient arthropathy is a type of transient arthritis. It encompasses various exact synonyms, including Transient arthropathy involving the forearm, hand, lower leg, multiple sites, pelvic region and thigh, shoulder region, and the upper arm.
Deep corneal vascularization is a type of corneal neovascularization and is exactly synonymous with Deep vascularization of the cornea.

Nutritional optic neuropathy is a type of optic neuritis and is also a type of condition that at least has the symptom of some acquired color vision deficiency. It is defined as an optic neuritis characterized by nutritional deficiency causing optic nerve dysfunction. This condition has symptoms including painless bilateral progressive decrease in visual acuity and color perception. Moreover, it has a material basis in nutritional deficits, especially of folate and vitamin B, which can be associated with restrictive diets and alcohol abuse.

Sodoku disease, also known exactly as Spirillary fever and relatedly known as Spirillosis, is a type of primary bacterial infectious disease. This disease results from an infection that has its material basis in Spirillum minus. It is transmitted by contact with urine or secretions from the mouth, eye, or nose of an infected animal or by the bite of an infected animal, especially a rat. Symptoms of Sodoku disease include chills, relapsing fever, rash, and joint pain, which are indicative of its nature as a disease that is at least transmitted by some form of contact transmission.
Trigeminal neuralgia is a type of trigeminal nerve disease and has exact synonyms Trifacial neuralgia and trifocal neuralgia.

Vaginal disease is the same as something that is an intersection of a disease and something that has at least one disease located in the vagina. It is a type of female reproductive system disease. Additionally, vaginal disease is defined as a female reproductive system disease that is located in the vagina.
Optic neuritis is a type of optic nerve disease defined as an optic nerve disease that results in inflammation located in the optic nerve, which may cause a complete or partial loss of vision.

Inflammatory spondylopathy is a type of spondylitis. In the disease classification system EC and in diseases classified elsewhere, it has exact synonyms: "Inflammatory spondylopathies" and "Inflammatory spondylopathy."

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:bullous_retinoschisis rdfs:subClassOf :retinoschisis .
text: bullous retinoschisis is a type of retinoschisis.

Pulmonary alveolar microlithiasis is a type of lung disease. It is defined as a lung disease characterized by the gradual accumulation of tiny fragments of calcium phosphate in the alveoli of the lungs.

Pulmonary hemosiderosis is a type of hemosiderosis and lung disease characterized by symptoms such as bleeding and dyspnea. It specifically affects the lungs, where the disease is located. Pulmonary hemosiderosis is also known by its exact synonyms: Idiopathic pulmonary hemosiderosis, brown induration, and brown lung. The condition is defined as a lung disease with an unknown etiology that impacts the lungs leading to bleeding from tiny alveolar capillaries. Diagnostic examination through sputum and bronchoalveolar lavage fluid can reveal hemosiderin-laden alveolar macrophages (siderophages), while lung biopsy shows numerous siderophages in the alveoli. Alveolar hemorrhage presents symptoms such as hemoptysis, shortness of breath, alveolar infiltrates on chest radiograph, and various degrees of anemia. After a bleeding episode, the alveolar macrophages convert the hemoglobin's iron into hemosiderin within 36-72 hours.

Hemosiderosis is a type of iron metabolism disease, which is defined as an iron metabolism disease that has a material basis in an accumulation of hemosiderin, an iron-storage complex, resulting in iron overload. It is exactly synonymous with haemosiderosis.
Pulmonary alveolar proteinosis is a type of lung disease characterized by the abnormal accumulation of surfactant within the alveoli, which interferes with gas exchange.
Postinflammatory pulmonary fibrosis is a type of pulmonary fibrosis, and it has an exact synonym: Post-inflammatory pulmonary fibrosis.

Episcleritis periodica fugax is a type of scleral disease that is characterized by painful inflammation of the episcleral tissues, importantly sparing the sclera itself. This condition exhibits several symptoms including inflammation, pain, photophobia (sensitivity to light), and a bloodshot eye. The definition of episcleritis periodica fugax further elaborates that it has symptoms such as pain, red eyes, photophobia, tearing, and blurry vision. Typically, this condition is self-limited but may be associated with vascular congestion within the superficial episcleral plexus. It can also be related to various factors such as autoimmune disease, connective tissue disease, malignancies, trauma, infection, and certain medications, notably topiramate and pamidronate.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:neurotrophic_keratoconjunctivitis rdfs:subClassOf :keratoconjunctivitis .
text: neurotrophic keratoconjunctivitis is a type of keratoconjunctivitis.
Pica disease is a type of eating disorder and is defined as an eating disorder that is characterized by an appetite for non-nutritive substances or food ingredients.

Bulimia nervosa is a type of eating disorder defined as an eating disorder characterized by the restraining of food intake for a period of time followed by an over intake or binging period that results in feelings of guilt and low self-esteem. It is also known exactly as hyperorexia nervosa.

Granulomatosis with polyangiitis is a type of autoimmune disease that affects various organs and systems within the body. It is recognized as a disease that impacts the blood, skin, kidneys, and lungs. This condition is associated with specific symptoms, including vasculitis and granulomatous inflammation. It has manifestations in several locations, notably affecting the skin, blood, lungs, and kidneys. Granulomatosis with polyangiitis is defined as an autoimmune disease characterized by necrotizing granulomatous inflammation of the upper and lower respiratory tract, glomerulonephritis, vasculitis, and the presence of antineutrophil cytoplasmatic autoantibodies (ANCAs) in patient sera. It primarily targets small and medium-size blood vessels, leading to significant complications in the lungs, kidneys, and skin as a result of an autoimmune attack by antineutrophil cytoplasmic antibodies. Furthermore, this disease is also known by its exact synonyms: Necrotizing respiratory granulomatosis and formerly as Wegener granulomatosis.

Factor VIII deficiency is a type of blood coagulation disease, which is also recognized as an X-linked recessive disease. It is characterized by having a material basis in some X-linked recessive inheritance. This condition is defined as a blood coagulation disease that results from Factor VIII deficiency, leading to the formation of fibrin-deficient clots, which significantly prolongs coagulation. Factor VIII deficiency is precisely synonymous with Congenital factor VIII disorder, Hemophilia A, Subhemophilia, and classic hemophilia A. Additionally, Factor VIII deficiency is exactly matched with MESH:D006467.
Dysthymic disorder is a type of mood disorder known as dysthymia, defined by the presence of a low mood almost daily over a span of at least two years.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:tympanosclerosis rdfs:subClassOf :tympanic_membrane_disease .
text: tympanosclerosis is a type of tympanic membrane disease.

Chagas disease, also known as American trypanosomiasis, is a type of trypanosomiasis with a material basis in Trypanosoma cruzi. This tropical parasitic disease is caused by the flagellate protozoan Trypanosoma cruzi, which is transmitted to humans and other mammals by an insect vector, specifically the blood-sucking assassin bugs of the subfamily Triatominae (family Reduviidae), most notably species belonging to the Triatoma, Rhodnius, and Panstrongylus genera. The disease is characterized by a variety of symptoms including myocarditis, body ache, loss of appetite, rash, headache, diarrhea, fever, vomiting, and fatigue. Additionally, Chagas disease is referred to by several exact synonyms: Chagas' disease, Chagas' disease with digestive system involvement, Chagas' disease with nervous system involvement, and Chagas' disease with other organ involvement.
Neurogenic bladder is a type of bladder disease and is exactly synonymous with Neuropathic bladder, neurogenic dysfunction of the urinary bladder, and neurogenic urinary bladder disorder.

Low compliance bladder is a type of bladder disease and it has several exact synonyms. These include Low bladder compliance, hyperactivity of bladder, hypertonic bladder, and hypertonicity of bladder.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:detrusor_sphincter_dyssynergia rdfs:subClassOf :bladder_disease .
text: detrusor sphincter dyssynergia is a type of bladder disease.

Alveolar echinococcosis is a type of echinococcosis that is also recognized as a disease affecting the liver, lungs, and brain. It is defined as an echinococcosis caused by the larvae of Echinococcus multilocularis, leading to a slow-growing, destructive tumor in the liver, with symptoms including abdominal pain, biliary obstruction, and possible metastatic lesions into the lungs and brain. Moreover, it intersects diseases that at least have their location in the liver, lungs, and brain. Alveolar echinococcosis is also known by its exact synonyms: Multilocular hydatid, alveolococcosis, and small fox tapeworm, and it has a related synonym, echinococcus multilocularis infection.

Lymphocytic choriomeningitis, also known exactly as LCM, Lymphocytic choriomeningitis virus encephalomyelitis, Lymphocytic meningitis, and Lymphocytic meningoencephalitis, is a type of viral infectious disease and brain disease. It has a material basis in Mammarenavirus choriomeningitidis and is transmitted by the common house mouse, Mus musculus. This disease's symptoms include fever, headache, malaise, nausea, vomiting, and it is located in the brain. Its comprehensive definition states it as a viral infectious disease resulting in infection located in the brain, or meninges, or both, caused by Mammarenavirus choriomeningitidis, transmitted by Mus musculus. The infection manifests symptoms such as fever, lack of appetite, headache, muscle aches, malaise, nausea, and vomiting.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:arachnoiditis rdfs:subClassOf :meningitis .
text: arachnoiditis is a type of meningitis.

Aseptic meningitis is a type of meningitis and is also a type of condition that involves at least some inflammation as a symptom. It is defined as a meningitis characterized by meningeal inflammation not caused by an identifiable bacterial pathogen in the cerebrospinal fluid, with a large majority of cases being caused by enteroviruses. Additionally, aseptic meningitis is exactly synonymous with acute aseptic meningitis.
Peripheral retinal degeneration is a type of retinal degeneration and is exactly synonymous with peripheral degeneration of the retina.
Pseudoretinitis pigmentosa is a type of peripheral retinal degeneration. It is also known exactly as secondary pigmentary degeneration of retina and secondary pigmentary retinal degeneration.
Senile reticular retinal degeneration is a type of peripheral retinal degeneration and it is also exactly synonymous with Senile reticular degeneration of the retina.
Blessig's cysts, also known exactly as Blessig cysts, Iwanoff's cysts, Microcystoid degeneration of the retina, and Microcystoid retinal degeneration, is a type of peripheral retinal degeneration.
Retinal lattice degeneration is a type of peripheral retinal degeneration and it is also exactly known as Palisade degeneration of the retina.
Cobblestone retinal degeneration, also precisely known as paving stone degeneration of retina or paving stone retinal degeneration, is a type of peripheral retinal degeneration.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:secondary_vitreoretinal_degeneration rdfs:subClassOf :peripheral_retinal_degeneration .
text: secondary vitreoretinal degeneration is a type of peripheral retinal degeneration.
An ulnar nerve lesion is a type of mononeuritis of the upper limb and also falls under mononeuritis multiplex. It is exactly synonymous with the term "Lesion of ulnar nerve."

Carpal tunnel syndrome is a type of nerve compression syndrome defined as a nerve compression syndrome characterized by pressure on the median nerve at the wrist, resulting in numbness, tingling, pain, and muscle weakness in the hand and forearm. It has exact synonyms including CTS - Carpal tunnel syndrome, Median nerve entrapment, and carpal tunnel median neuropathy.

Fascioloidiasis is a type of parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease, defined as a parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves the parasitic infection of the liver of a variety of wild and domestic ruminants by Fascioloides magna.
A radial nerve lesion, which is a type of radial neuropathy, is also exactly synonymous with "Lesion of radial nerve" and "Radial nerve lesions."

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:radial_neuropathy rdfs:subClassOf :mononeuropathy .
text: radial neuropathy is a type of mononeuropathy.
Dyshormonogenic goiter is a type of goiter and it has an exact synonym, dyshormonogenic goitre.

Goiter is a type of thyroid gland disease characterized by an abnormal enlargement of the thyroid gland. It is also known as goitre and has an exact match in the Medical Subject Headings (MESH) with the identifier D006042.

Common Variable Immunodeficiency (CVID) is a type of disease that falls into several categories: it is considered an autosomal recessive disease, agammaglobulinemia, and an autoimmune disease. It is also characterized by having a material basis in autosomal recessive inheritance and a phenotype that includes decreased circulating antibody levels. CVID is defined as an agammaglobulinemia characterized by low immunoglobulin (Ig) levels with phenotypically normal B cells that can proliferate but do not develop into Ig-producing cells. This results in insufficient production of antibodies necessary to respond to exposure to pathogens. Additionally, CVID is known by several exact synonyms, including CVID, acquired agammaglobulinemia, acquired hypogammaglobulinemia, common variable agammaglobulinemia, and sporadic hypogammaglobulinemia.

Tinea corporis is a type of skin disease and a type of dermatophytosis, which is characterized by its relation to ascomycota fungi and the presence of symptoms such as a rash. It specifically affects the zone of skin and the stratum corneum of the epidermis. Tinea corporis is defined as a dermatophytosis that results in a fungal infection located in the skin, precisely limited to the stratum corneum of the epidermis. This condition has a material basis in Ascomycota fungi that belong to a group known as dermatophytes. It is associated with symptoms like itching and a red-colored skin rash, where the border of the rash lesions appears scaly. Additionally, tinea corporis is exactly synonymous with Dermatophytosis of the trunk and dermatophytosis of the body.

Echinostomiasis is a type of parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves parasitic infection of the intestine by Echinostoma species. This condition has a material basis in some echinostoma and is characterized by symptoms such as abdominal pain, nausea, diarrhea, fever, and vomiting. It is also known by its exact synonym, Infection by Echinochasmus.

Otosclerosis is a type of inner ear disease and an autosomal dominant disease, specifically a condition that at least has a material basis in some autosomal dominant inheritance. It is defined as an otitis interna characterized by isolated endochondral bone sclerosis of the labyrinthine capsule. Otosclerosis has an exact match with the MESH code D010040.

Dicrocoeliasis is a type of parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves the parasitic infection of the bile ducts of the liver by Dicrocoelium dendriticum. This disease is also known as a disease due to Dicrocoeliidae. It is characterized by symptoms such as hepatic abscesses, general abscesses, and cholecystitis, along with upper abdominal pain.

Descending colon cancer is the same as something that intersects cancer and a disease located at the descending colon. It is a type of colon cancer and has exact synonyms: Ca descending colon, malignant neoplasm of left colon, and malignant tumor of descending colon.

Splenic flexure cancer is equivalent to an intersection of cancer and diseases located at the splenic flexure of the colon. It is a type of descending colon cancer. Furthermore, splenic flexure cancer is exactly synonymous with Ca splenic flexure - colon, malignant neoplasm of splenic flexure, and malignant tumor of splenic flexure.

Sigmoid colon cancer is the same as something that intersects cancer and something that, at the very least, is a disease located in the sigmoid colon. It is a type of colon cancer. Additionally, sigmoid colon cancer has exact synonyms, including "Ca sigmoid colon" and "malignant tumor of sigmoid colon."

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:superficial_keratitis rdfs:subClassOf :keratitis .
text: superficial keratitis is a type of keratitis.

Punctate epithelial keratoconjunctivitis is a type of keratoconjunctivitis and has exact synonyms Punctate keratitis, Thygeson superficial punctate keratitis, and Thygeson's superficial punctate keratitis.

Dengue disease is a type of viral infectious disease that has a material basis in the Dengue virus, which includes four serotypes (Dengue virus 1, 2, 3, and 4) transmitted by the bite of an Aedes mosquito. This disease is characterized by several symptoms, including bleeding, joint pain, severe headache, rash, fever, muscle pain, and bone pain. It is defined as a viral infectious disease that results in infection, specifically caused by the Dengue virus [NCBITaxon:12637], and manifests symptoms such as fever, severe headache, severe pain behind the eyes, joint pain, muscle and bone pain, rash, and mild bleeding. Dengue disease is also known by several exact synonyms, including Dengue Fever, breakbone fever, and classic dengue, with a related synonym being classical dengue.

Dengue hemorrhagic fever (DHF) is a type of dengue disease that occurs when a person experiences a second infection with a heterologous Dengue virus serotype transmitted by an Aedes mosquito bite. It is characterized by having a material basis in some dengue virus and exhibits symptoms such as thrombocytopenia and high fever. The condition is defined by the presence of hemorrhagic lesions of the skin, thrombocytopenia, a reduction in the fluid part of the blood, and high fever. DHF is also known by its exact synonym "DHF" and its related synonym "Dengue haemorrhagic fever."

Filarial elephantiasis is a type of filariasis and a skin disease. It is characterized by several phenotypes including hyperkeratosis and epidermal thickening. The disease manifests through various symptoms such as lymphangitis, epididymitis, fever, abscess, and lymphadenitis, and specifically affects the zone of skin. It is defined as a filariasis characterized by the thickening of the skin and underlying tissues, notably in the legs, male genitals, and female breasts. This condition is caused by thread-like parasitic worms, namely Wuchereria bancrofti, Brugia malayi, or Brugia timori, which inhabit the lymphatics and are transmitted by mosquitoes. Acute symptoms include fever, lymphadenitis, lymphangitis, funiculitis, and epididymitis, whereas chronic symptoms encompass abscesses, hyperkeratosis, polyarthritis, hydroceles, lymphedema, and elephantiasis. Additionally, filarial elephantiasis is also known by exact synonyms such as Bancroftian elephantiasis, Bancroftian filarial chyluria, Lymphatic filariasis, and elephantiasis of the eyelid.

Oligohydramnios is a type of placenta disease characterized by a deficiency of amniotic fluid, which can sometimes result in an embryonic defect through adherence between the embryo and amnion. It is also exactly synonymous with "Oligohydramnios - delivered," "antepartum oligohydramnios," and "delivered oligohydramnios."

Lewy body dementia is a type of dementia characterized by the development of abnormal proteinaceous (alpha-synuclein) cytoplasmic inclusions, known as Lewy bodies, throughout the brain, leading to a progressive decline in mental abilities. It is also precisely referred to as Dementia with Lewy bodies, Diffuse Lewy body disease, Lewy body disease, and Senile dementia of the Lewy body type.

Cartilage disease is the same as something that is an intersection of a disease and something that has a location in some cartilage tissue. It is a type of connective tissue disease and is defined as a connective tissue disease that is located in cartilage. Furthermore, cartilage disease has exact synonyms, including Cartilage disorder and Chondropathy.
Specific bursitis, often of occupational origin, is a type of bursitis and it has an exact synonym: Specific bursitides often of occupational origin.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:plica_syndrome rdfs:subClassOf :arthropathy .
text: plica syndrome is a type of arthropathy.
Cascade stomach is a type of stomach disease, which is also precisely known as Hourglass stricture or stenosis of the stomach.

Primary biliary cholangitis is a type of autoimmune disease affecting the gastrointestinal tract and is also a form of liver cirrhosis. It is characterized by having at least a phenotype that includes abnormal immunoglobulin levels. The condition is defined as liver cirrhosis marked by the chronic and slow progressive destruction of intrahepatic bile ducts. Primary biliary cholangitis is exactly synonymous with several terms, including biliary liver cirrhosis, cholestatic cirrhosis, chronic nonsuppurative destructive cholangitis, and primary biliary cirrhosis.
Bile reflux is a type of biliary tract disease characterized by the flow of bile up into the stomach and/or esophagus.

Anal margin squamous cell carcinoma is a type of squamous cell carcinoma, anal margin carcinoma, and something that at least derives from some squamous epithelial cell. It has the exact synonym Perianal skin squamous cell carcinoma.
Beta thalassemia is a type of thalassemia, characterized by the reduced or absent synthesis of the beta globin chains of hemoglobin. Moreover, it has a narrower match with MESH:D017086.
Histoplasmosis meningitis, which is a type of fungal meningitis, is exactly synonymous with Histoplasmosis with meningitis.

Testicular lymphoma is a type of lymphoma and a type of testicular cancer, which is characterized by having at least some material basis in lymphocytes. Additionally, it is exactly synonymous with lymphoma of the testis and malignant lymphoma of the testis.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:medulloadrenal_hyperfunction rdfs:subClassOf :adrenal_gland_disease .
text: medulloadrenal hyperfunction is a type of adrenal gland disease.

Hemophilia B is a type of blood coagulation disease and an X-linked recessive disease, which essentially has a material basis in X-linked recessive inheritance. It is defined as a blood coagulation disorder caused by Factor IX deficiency, leading to significantly prolonged coagulation times, and inherited as an X-linked recessive trait. Hemophilia B is exactly synonymous with Congenital Factor IX deficiency, Congenital Factor IX disorder, deficiency, functional Factor IX, and Factor IX deficiency.
Chronic salpingo oophoritis is a type of salpingo oophoritis and it has exact synonyms: chronic salpingitis and oophoritis, as well as chronic salpingitis/oophoritis.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:neutropenia rdfs:subClassOf :agranulocytosis .
text: neutropenia is a type of agranulocytosis.

Coloboma is a type of eye disease characterized by missing pieces of tissue in structures that form the eye, such as the iris, retina, choroid, or optic disc. It has exact synonyms including coloboma of eye, coloboma of macula, and congenital ocular coloboma.

Aniridia is a type of iris disease, which is characterized by a complete or partial absence of the colored part of the eye. It is also known by its exact synonyms, Aplasia of iris and isolated aniridia. Aniridia is precisely matched with several medical identifiers: GARD:5816, ICD10CM:Q13.1, ICD9CM:743.45, MESH:D015783, NCI:C84563, OMIM:PS106210, ORDO:250923, and UMLS_CUI:C0003076.
Anisometropia is a type of refractive error, which has an exact match with MESH:D015858.

Cutaneous diphtheria is a type of pyoderma, defined as a milder form of diphtheria that is restricted to the skin, producing shallow skin ulcers. It is caused by direct physical contact with individuals infected with Corynebacterium diphtheriae, as the bacteria releases the diphtheria toxin.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:malignant_tumor_of_undescended_testis rdfs:subClassOf :testicular_cancer ;
    :has_exact_synonym "malignant neoplasm of retained testis"@en,
        "malignant neoplasm of undescended testis"@en,
        "malignant tumor of retained testis"@en,
        "malignant tumour of retained testis"@en,
        "malignant tumour of undescended testis"@en .
text: Malignant tumor of undescended testis is a type of testicular cancer and has exact synonyms including malignant neoplasm of retained testis, malignant neoplasm of undescended testis, malignant tumor of retained testis, malignant tumour of retained testis, and malignant tumour of undescended testis.

Femoral vein thrombophlebitis is identified as an intersection of conditions that are a type of thrombophlebitis and any disease located in the femoral vein. It is specifically a type of thrombophlebitis and also characterized as a condition that has phlebitis as a symptom. Furthermore, femoral vein thrombophlebitis is exactly synonymous with Phlebitis and thrombophlebitis of the femoral vein, Thrombophlebitis of the deep femoral vein, and Thrombophlebitis of the femoral vein.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:testicular_leukemia rdfs:subClassOf :testicular_cancer .
text: testicular leukemia is a type of testicular cancer.

Crimean Congo Hemorrhagic Fever (CCHF) is a type of viral infectious disease with a material basis in Orthonairovirus haemorrhagiae. It is transmitted by Hyalomma ticks. The symptoms of CCHF include backache, hematuria (blood in urine), joint pain, hematochezia (blood in feces), bloodshot eyes, epistaxis (nosebleeds), headache, jaundice, petechiae (small red or purple spots on the body), high fever, and vomiting. Additionally, the disease is defined as a viral infectious hemorrhagic fever that is transmitted by Hyalomma ticks and can result in symptoms such as headache, high fever, back pain, joint pain, stomach pain, vomiting, red eyes, flushed face, red throat, petechiae on the palate, jaundice, nosebleeds, and blood in the feces and urine. The disease also has exact synonyms: CHF Congo virus, Congo-Crimean Hemorrhagic Fever, and Crimean hemorrhagic fever.

Paranoid schizophrenia is a type of schizophrenia that is characterized by delusions or auditory hallucinations of persecution or being plotted against, without thought disorder, disorganized behavior, or affective flattening. It is a type of condition that at least has symptoms of some hallucination. Paranoid schizophrenia is also known by exact synonyms such as Paranoid type schizophrenia, Paraphrenia - late, Paraphrenic schizophrenia, Chronic paranoid schizophrenia, and Paranoid type schizophrenia subchronic state.

Atypical depressive disorder is a type of mood disorder that is characterized by mood reactivity and positivity, significant weight gain or increased appetite, excessive sleep or somnolence, a sensation of heaviness in limbs known as leaden paralysis, and significant social impairment as a consequence of hypersensitivity to perceived interpersonal rejection. This disorder is also known by its exact synonym, Atypical depression. It is associated with at least the symptoms of some paralysis and some hypersomnia.

Vogt-Koyanagi-Harada disease is a type of autoimmune disease of skin and connective tissue, which also manifests symptoms of meningitis. This condition specifically affects areas that are an intersection of skin and connective tissue. It is defined as an autoimmune disease caused by a T helper cell mediated autoimmune attack on melanocytes, leading to inflammation inside the eye, whitening of hair, skin pigment loss, and meningitis. Vogt-Koyanagi-Harada disease is also known by exact synonyms such as Harada's disease, Vogt-Koyanagi syndrome, and uveomeningoencephalitic syndrome.

Intrahepatic gall duct cancer, a type of gallbladder cancer, is also precisely known by several synonyms including Ca intrahepatic bile ducts, malignant neoplasm of intrahepatic bile ducts, malignant neoplasm of intrahepatic biliary passages, and malignant neoplasm of intrahepatic gall duct.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:conjunctival_pigmentation rdfs:subClassOf :pigmentation_disease .
text: conjunctival pigmentation is a type of pigmentation disease.
Bloch Sulzberger syndrome, which is a type of pigmentation disease, is also exactly known as Incontinentia Pigmenti and Incontinentia Pigmenti syndrome.

Vitiligo is a type of autoimmune disease that affects the skin and connective tissue, found specifically at the intersection zone of skin and connective tissue. It is defined as an autoimmune disease that causes depigmentation of patches of skin resulting from the loss of function or death of melanocytes.
Anterior corneal pigmentation is a type of corneal deposit and has the exact synonym "Anterior corneal pigmentations."

Dubin Johnson syndrome is a type of bilirubin metabolic disorder defined as a condition involving elevated levels of unconjugated bilirubin without elevation of liver alanine transaminase and aspartate transaminase enzymes. This occurs due to the deficient ability of hepatocytes to secrete conjugated bilirubin into the bile. Additionally, Dubin Johnson syndrome is exactly synonymous with both "Dubin Johnson syndrome" itself and "chronic idiopathic jaundice."
Urticaria pigmentosa is a type of cutaneous mastocytosis and has the exact synonym UP/MPCM. Additionally, it exactly matches MESH:D014582.
Stromal corneal pigmentation is a type of pigmentation disease, and it has an exact synonym: Stromal corneal pigmentations.

Granular corneal dystrophy is a type of autosomal dominant disease, an epithelial stromal TGFBI dystrophy, and something that at least has a material basis in some autosomal dominant inheritance. It is defined as an epithelial-stromal TGFBI dystrophy characterized by the progressive accumulation of deposits within the layers of the cornea.

Cough variant asthma is a type of chronic asthma characterized by a chronic nonproductive cough without shortness of breath. It is also a type of condition that, at a minimum, includes coughing as a symptom.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:kyphoscoliotic_heart_disease rdfs:subClassOf :chronic_pulmonary_heart_disease .
text: kyphoscoliotic heart disease is a type of chronic pulmonary heart disease.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:chronic_pulmonary_heart_disease rdfs:subClassOf :cor_pulmonale .
text: chronic pulmonary heart disease is a type of cor pulmonale.

Marasmus is a type of protein-energy malnutrition that is also known as nutritional atrophy or nutritional marasmus. It is characterized by severe caloric deprivation and exhibits symptoms such as emaciation, hypothermia, bradycardia, weight gain, loss of height, constipation, and decreased metabolism. The condition has a material basis in severe caloric deprivation.
Transvestism is a type of fetishism and has exact synonyms including Dual-role transvestism, Fetishistic transvestism, Transvestic fetishism, and cross-dresser.
Hematocele of tunica vaginalis testis is a type of testicular disease, which is a condition that affects the testis. It has exact synonyms "Hematocele" and "male hematocele".
Male genital organ stricture, which has the exact synonym "Stricture of male genital organs," is a type of male reproductive system disease.
Male genital organ vascular disease is a type of male reproductive system disease and has the exact synonym "vascular disorder of male genital organs."

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:male_infertility rdfs:subClassOf :male_reproductive_system_disease .
text: male infertility is a type of male reproductive system disease.
Varicocele is a type of pelvic varices and has an exact synonym, Scrotal varices. It is a condition that occurs in the spermatic cord, which is a type of location where at least one disease is found.
Retroperitoneal lymphoma is a type of lymphoma and also a type of retroperitoneal cancer. Furthermore, it is a type of something that at least has a material basis in some lymphocyte.

Gender incongruence is a type of sexual health disorder and is defined as a conflict between a person's actual physical gender and the gender that person identifies with. It has exact synonyms, including gender dysphoria, gender identity disorder, and transsexualism.
Retroperitoneal sarcoma is a type of retroperitoneal cancer, defined as a malignant retroperitoneal cancer and sarcoma located in the retroperitoneal space.

Retroperitoneum carcinoma is a type of carcinoma, retroperitoneal cancer, and something that at least derives from some epithelial cell. It has the exact synonym "carcinoma of Retroperitoneum" and a related synonym "carcinoma of the retroperitoneum."

Osteogenesis imperfecta is a type of osteochondrodysplasia with a definition that states it as an osteochondrodysplasia based on a deficiency in type-I collagen, leading to brittle bones and defective connective tissue. It is exactly synonymous with Lobstein's syndrome, Osteopsathyrosis, Vrolik's disease, and brittle bone disease. Moreover, it has a related synonym, Fragilitas ossium.
Primary eye hypotony is a type of ocular hypotension and is exactly synonymous with primary hypotony of the eye.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:fetishism rdfs:subClassOf :paraphilia_disorder .
text: fetishism is a type of paraphilia disorder.

Alcoholic hepatitis is a type of hepatitis and also a type of something that has alcohol as at least one disease driver. Moreover, alcoholic hepatitis has the exact synonyms acute alcoholic hepatitis and acute alcoholic liver disease.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:prostatocystitis rdfs:subClassOf :cystitis .
text: prostatocystitis is a type of cystitis.

Viral labyrinthitis is a type of labyrinthitis and also a type of viral infectious disease that has its material basis in some viruses. It is characterized by symptoms such as loss of balance, tinnitus, nausea, dizziness, and vomiting. The condition is defined as a labyrinthitis which involves viral infection of the inner ear through the upper airway or the bloodstream, leading to potential hearing loss and ringing in the ears. If the virus affects the vestibular system, it can result in dizziness, severe vertigo with nausea and vomiting, and imbalance. Viral labyrinthitis is also known by its exact synonym, Epidemic vertigo.

Patulous eustachian tube is a type of eustachian tube disease defined as a disorder where the eustachian tube is wider, allowing a larger bolus of bacteria-laden material from the nasopharynx during an infection to enter the middle ear, leading to a more severe infection.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:endocrine_exophthalmos rdfs:subClassOf :orbital_disease .
text: endocrine exophthalmos is a type of orbital disease.
Lateral displacement of the eye, which has the exact synonym "Lateral displacement of globe," is a type of orbital disease.

Graves' disease is a type of autoimmune disease of the endocrine system, characterized by the production of an excessive amount of thyroid hormones, which occurs in the thyroid gland. This condition is also known by several synonyms; it is exactly synonymous with "Grave's disease," "Graves disease," and "exophthalmic goiter." Additionally, it has a related synonym, "Basedow's disease."

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:thyrotoxic_exophthalmos rdfs:subClassOf :endocrine_exophthalmos .
text: thyrotoxic exophthalmos is a type of endocrine exophthalmos.
Intermittent proptosis, which has the exact synonym intermittent exophthalmos, is a type of orbital disease.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:pulsating_exophthalmos rdfs:subClassOf :orbital_disease .
text: pulsating exophthalmos is a type of orbital disease.

Malaria is defined as a parasitic protozoa infectious disease characterized as a vector-borne infectious disease caused by the presence of protozoan parasites of the genus Plasmodium in the red blood cells. It is transmitted from an infected to an uninfected individual by the bite of anopheline mosquitoes. This disease is marked by periodic attacks of chills and fever that coincide with the mass destruction of blood cells and the release of toxic substances by the parasite at the end of each reproductive cycle. Malaria is equivalent to an intersection of a disease that is both a parasitic protozoa infectious disease and has a material basis at least in some form of Plasmodium. Moreover, malaria is a type of disease that has at least one symptom, specifically chills, and it also has an exact synonym, which is induced malaria.

Prolapse of the urethra is a condition that falls under several categories: it is a type of prolapse of female genital organ, a type of urethral disease, and a type of condition where the disease is located in the urethra. It is defined as a prolapse of the female genital organ that is characterized by the descent of the urethra from its normal anatomic location toward or through the vaginal opening. Additionally, prolapse of the urethra is exactly synonymous with Urethrocele.

Corneal degeneration is the same as something that is an intersection of eye degenerative disease and something that is a disease located at least in the cornea. It is a type of corneal disease and also a type of eye degenerative disease.

Bronchopneumonia is a type of pneumonia, which is characterized as a disease that features some aspect of pneumonia. It is specifically defined as a pneumonia involving inflammation of the lungs that begins in the terminal bronchioles. These bronchioles become clogged with thick mucus that forms consolidated patches in adjacent lobules, and it is caused by bacteria and viruses. Furthermore, bronchopneumonia is also known by exact synonyms such as chest infection - bronchopneumonia, bronchial pneumonia, and lobular pneumonia.

Juvenile spinal muscular atrophy is a type of childhood spinal muscular atrophy characterized by symptoms such as muscle weakness. It is also known for its onset during the young adult phase. Specifically, this condition is defined as a childhood spinal muscular atrophy that begins after 18 months of age, characterized by muscle weakness after early childhood, and the capability to stand and walk. This condition is caused by homozygous or compound heterozygous mutations in the SMN1 gene on chromosome 5q13. Furthermore, juvenile spinal muscular atrophy is also known by several exact synonyms, including Kugelberg-Welander disease, SMA3, Spinal Muscular Atrophy Type 3, and Type III Spinal Muscular Atrophy.

Spinal muscular atrophy is a type of motor neuron disease and is defined as a degenerative neuromuscular disease characterized by lower motor neuron degeneration associated with progressive muscle weakness and atrophy. It is also a type of condition that at least has symptoms of muscle weakness and progressive weakness.
Complex partial epilepsy, a type of focal epilepsy, is exactly synonymous with Complex partial epileptic seizure, epilepsy, psychomotor, and psychomotor epilepsy.

Dysentery is an intestinal infectious disease and a type of condition that always has diarrhea as a symptom. It is defined as an intestinal infectious disease that involves inflammation of the intestines, especially the colon, due to chemical irritants, bacteria, protozoa, or parasitic worms, which results in severe diarrhea with the passage of mucus and blood. Additionally, dysentery has an exact synonym, which is Infectious diarrhea.

Shigellosis, also known as bacillary dysentery, is identified as a primary bacterial infectious disease and a colonic disease. It is characterized by being an intersection of a bacterial infectious disease and diseases that are located in the colon. Furthermore, shigellosis is a disease that is transmitted through vehicle-borne ingestion transmission and is known to have diarrhea as a symptom. The definition of shigellosis encompasses a primary bacterial infectious disease that results in infection located in the epithelium of the colon. It is caused by one of the following bacteria: Shigella boydii, Shigella dysenteriae, Shigella flexneri, or Shigella sonnei. These bacteria produce toxins that attack the lining of the large intestine, leading to swelling, ulcers on the intestinal wall, and bloody diarrhea. The mode of transmission is through the ingestion of food and water contaminated with feces. Shigellosis is also referred to by several exact synonyms, including Shigella boydii infectious disease, Shigella flexneri infectious disease, Shigella gastroenteritis, and Shigella sonnei infectious disease.

Balantidiasis is a type of parasitic protozoa infectious disease characterized by various symptoms including abdominal cramps, abdominal pain, nausea, and diarrhea. It is defined as a parasitic protozoa infectious disease caused by the infection of Balantidium coli. The trophozoites of this parasite attack the intestinal epithelium, leading to the creation of ulcers and causing bloody diarrhea. The infection is associated with symptoms such as cramping, abdominal pain, nausea, and foul breath. Additionally, balantidiasis is precisely matched with the Medical Subject Headings (MESH) identifier D001447.

Nephrogenic diabetes insipidus is a type of diabetes insipidus that is characterized by a complete or partial resistance of the kidneys to vasopressin (ADH). It is a type of condition that at least has the symptom of polyuria. Additionally, nephrogenic diabetes insipidus is also known by the related synonym vasopressin-resistant diabetes insipidus.

Neurohypophyseal diabetes insipidus, also known exactly as pituitary diabetes insipidus, vasopressin deficiency, and vasopressin defective diabetes insipidus, is a type of autosomal dominant disease and central diabetes insipidus. It is characterized by a condition that at least has a material basis in some form of autosomal dominant inheritance. The definition of neurohypophyseal diabetes insipidus is a central diabetes insipidus that is characterized by excessive urination (polyuria) and excessive thirst (polydipsia) due to a deficiency in vasopressin synthesis. This condition has a material basis in a heterozygous mutation in the arginine vasopressin gene (AVP) on chromosome 20p13.
