@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:spastic_entropion rdfs:subClassOf :entropion .
text: spastic entropion is a type of entropion.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:entropion rdfs:subClassOf :eyelid_disease .
text: entropion is a type of eyelid disease.

Pathological gambling is a type of impulse control disorder that involves the uncontrollable impulse to gamble, irrespective of the interference the behavior has on the individual's life. It is also exactly synonymous with compulsive gambling.
Leukemia is a type of hematologic cancer and is defined as a cancer that affects the blood or bone marrow, characterized by an abnormal proliferation of blood cells.

Kleptomania is a type of impulse control disorder that has the definition of being an impulse control disorder involving the repeated impulse to steal for no great gain, even when the individual has sufficient money to pay for the item and no need for what is stolen. Additionally, kleptomania has the exact synonym "Pathological stealing."

Intermittent explosive disorder is a type of impulse control disorder and is defined as an impulse control disorder that involves the episodic inability to control violent impulses, exhibiting a disproportionate degree of aggressiveness. Additionally, it is also known by the exact synonym, explosive personality disorder.

Pyromania is a type of impulse control disorder that involves the uncontrollable impulse to repeatedly set fires with no obvious motive. It is also known by its exact synonyms, which include "Pathological firesetting" and "firesetting behavior."

Tinea pedis is a type of skin disease and a form of dermatophytosis. It is characterized by having a material basis in fungi, specifically in the union of Epidermophyton and Trichophyton. Moreover, tinea pedis is associated with symptoms such as skin desquamation and has its disease location primarily on the skin, particularly on the foot. This condition is defined as a dermatophytosis that results in a fungal infection located in the skin of the foot, especially between the toes. It is caused by Trichophyton or Epidermophyton and presents symptoms like fissures, scaling, maceration, and eroded areas between the toes and on the plantar surface of the foot. Additionally, tinea pedis is also known by its exact synonyms, Athlete's foot and Dermatophytosis of foot, and has a related synonym, ringworm of foot.
Luxation of the globe, which is a type of globe disease, has the exact synonym "Luxation of eye."
Globe disease is a type of eye disease that is defined as an eye disease involving the globe of the eye.
Thyrocalcitonin secretion disease, which is a type of thyroid gland disease, has the exact synonym "disorder of thyrocalcitonin secretion."

Labia minora cancer is identical to an intersection of something that is cancer and something that is at least a disease located in the labium minora. It is a type of vulva cancer and also a type of skin cancer. The definition of labia minora cancer is a vulva cancer that is located in the labium minora. Furthermore, it has exact synonyms including malignant neoplasm of labia minora, malignant neoplasm of labium minus, and malignant tumor of Labia Minora.
Conjugate gaze palsy, which is a type of strabismus, has the exact synonym Palsy of conjugate gaze.
Aplastic anemia is a type of anemia that is characterized by a deficiency of red blood cells, white blood cells, and platelets produced by the bone marrow.

Vulva cancer is equivalent to an intersection of cancer and a disease located in the mammalian vulva, and it is a type of female reproductive organ cancer as well as a type of vulvar disease. It is defined as a female reproductive organ cancer that is located in the vulva. Furthermore, vulva cancer has various exact synonyms, including Ca vulva, Vulvar tumor, malignant Vulvar tumor, malignant neoplasm of vulva, malignant tumor of vulva, neoplasm of vulva, vulval cancer, vulval neoplasm, and vulvar neoplasm.

Pancytopenia is a type of anemia and it is defined as an anemia that is characterized by a reduction in the number of red blood cells, white blood cells, and platelets. Additionally, pancytopenia has an exact match with MESH:D010198.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:sulfhemoglobinemia rdfs:subClassOf :blood_protein_disease .
text: sulfhemoglobinemia is a type of blood protein disease.

Secondary hyperparathyroidism of renal origin is a type of secondary hyperparathyroidism and is also a type of kidney disease. It is characterized by something that has at least a disease located in some kidney. Additionally, secondary hyperparathyroidism of renal origin is exactly synonymous with hyperparathyroidism due to renal insufficiency.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:secondary_hyperparathyroidism rdfs:subClassOf :hyperparathyroidism .
text: secondary hyperparathyroidism is a type of hyperparathyroidism.

Blood coagulation disease is a type of hematopoietic system disease characterized by abnormal blood clotting or bleeding. It is exactly synonymous with coagulation protein disease, postpartum coagulation defect, and postpartum coagulation defect with delivery. Furthermore, blood coagulation disease has a narrow synonym, inherited blood coagulation disease.

Capillariasis is a type of disease that affects various organs including the liver, intestine, and lungs. It falls under the category of parasitic helminthiasis infectious diseases. Specifically, it is associated with infections in the intestine, liver, and lungs caused by species of Capillaria. This condition is also known as Capillaria infection. Moreover, the disease is characterized by having a material basis in Capillaria species. Capillariasis is defined as a parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease involving the infection of the intestine, liver, and lungs by Capillaria species.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:pes_anserinus_tendinitis_or_bursitis rdfs:subClassOf :enthesopathy .
text: pes anserinus tendinitis or bursitis is a type of enthesopathy.
Ocular hyperemia is a type of conjunctival disease and it is exactly synonymous with both hyperEMIA eye and hyperemia of conjunctiva.

Vagus nerve disease is the same as something that intersects with a disease and something that has at least one disease located in the vagus nerve. Furthermore, vagus nerve disease is categorized as a type of glossopharyngeal nerve disease. Additionally, it has several exact synonyms, including Vagus nerve disorder, disorder of pneumogastric [10th] nerve, disorder of vagal nerve, and disorder of vagus nerve.

Vagina leiomyoma is a type of vaginal benign neoplasm and also a type of leiomyoma, which at least derives from some smooth muscle cell and has its location in the vagina. It is defined as a vaginal benign neoplasm that is a benign tumor of smooth muscle cells. Additionally, vagina leiomyoma has an exact synonym: leiomyoma of the vagina.

Bell's palsy is a type of facial paralysis defined as a facial paralysis resulting from dysfunction in the cranial nerve VII (facial nerve). It also has exact synonyms including Bell palsy and Bell's (facial) palsy.

Tuberculous epididymitis is a type of epididymis disease, and it is also classified under urogenital tuberculosis. This condition is characterized by at least having some pain as a symptom and is a disease that occurs in the epididymis. The definition of tuberculous epididymitis is an urogenital tuberculosis that is located in the epididymis, and it manifests symptoms including pain and scrotal swelling.

Retinal ischemia is a type of retinal vascular disease and a form of ischemia that specifically affects the retina, indicating its classification within diseases located in the retina. It is defined as an ischemia characterized by a restriction in blood supply to the retina.
Retinal perforation is a type of retinal detachment and it has exact synonyms: Retinal break, Retinal dialysis, and Retinal tear.

Trichuriasis, also known as infection by Trichuris trichura, Trichuriasis infection, Whipworm disease, or Trichuris trichiura infection, is a type of intestinal disease, parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease, and is characterized by being caused at least partially by Trichuris trichiura. It is an affliction that typically has its location in the intestine and features symptoms such as abdominal pain, diarrhea, rectal prolapse, and can lead to growth retardation. The disease is defined as a parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that results from a parasitic infection in the intestines of humans, originating from the ingestion of food contaminated with soil that carries the eggs of Trichuris trichiura.

Bagassosis is a type of extrinsic allergic alveolitis, which is an industrial disease characterized by symptoms such as cough, difficult breathing, chills, fever, and prolonged weakness. These symptoms are caused by the inhalation of the dust of bagasse containing thermophilic actinomycetes. Additionally, bagassosis is known by the exact synonym sugar cane worker pneumonitis.
A plantar nerve lesion is a type of mononeuritis of the lower limb and is exactly synonymous with the lesion of the plantar nerve.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:tarsal_tunnel_syndrome rdfs:subClassOf :tibial_neuropathy .
text: tarsal tunnel syndrome is a type of tibial neuropathy.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:common_peroneal_nerve_lesion rdfs:subClassOf :mononeuritis_of_lower_limb .
text: common peroneal nerve lesion is a type of mononeuritis of lower limb.

A lesion of the sciatic nerve is equivalent to an intersection of diseases, specifically those that at least have the location of the sciatic nerve. Furthermore, a lesion of the sciatic nerve is classified as a type of mononeuritis of the lower limb.

Tibial nerve palsy is the same as a disease that intersects with another condition, which is at least a disease located in the tibial nerve. Moreover, tibial nerve palsy is a type of mononeuritis of the lower limb.

Von Willebrand's disease is a type of blood coagulation disease characterized by a hereditary abnormality that slows the blood clotting process. This arises from a qualitative or quantitative deficiency of von Willebrand factor (vWF), a multimeric protein essential for platelet adhesion. It is also known by several exact synonyms, including vascular hemophilia, vascular pseudohemophilia, von Willebrand disease, von Willebrand disorder, von Willebrand's-Jurgens' disease, and von Willebrand-Jrgens disease.
Hypermobility of the coccyx is a type of spondyloarthropathy. It has exact synonyms, including Coccygeal hypermobility syndrome and hypermobility of the coccyx.

Trichostrongylosis is a type of trichostrongyloidiasis and also a type of condition that at least has the symptom of diarrhea. It is defined as a trichostrongyloidiasis that involves infection of the small intestine with Trichostrongylus colubriformis or Trichostrongylus axei, resulting in symptoms such as abdominal pain, diarrhea, anorexia, headache, fatigue, anemia, and eosinophilia. Trichostrongylosis has exact synonyms including Infection by Trichostrongylus, Infection by Trichostrongylus species, and Trichostrongyliasis. Furthermore, it has an exact match with the MESH code D014253.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:atrophic_nonflaccid_tympanic_membrane rdfs:subClassOf :tympanic_membrane_disease .
text: atrophic nonflaccid tympanic membrane is a type of tympanic membrane disease.

Hepatitis A is a type of viral infectious disease that has a material basis in Hepatovirus A. It is defined as a viral infectious disease resulting in inflammation located in the liver, transmitted by ingestion of contaminated food or water, or by direct contact with an infected person. The symptoms of Hepatitis A include fever, fatigue, loss of appetite, nausea, vomiting, abdominal pain, acholic (clay-colored) stool, joint pain, liver inflammation, jaundice, and in some cases, fever. Hepatitis A is also known by its exact synonym, Viral Hepatitis, type A, and has a related synonym, Viral Hepatitis A.

Trichostrongyloidiasis is a type of parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease, which is defined as a parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves the parasitic infection of animals and humans by nematodes of the superfamily Trichostrongyloidea.
Hepatic coma, which is a type of hepatic encephalopathy, has the exact synonym Hepatocerebral intoxication.

Hemolytic uremic syndrome is a type of kidney disease that is characterized by hemolytic anemia, thrombocytopenia, and renal failure caused by platelet thrombi in the microcirculation of the kidney and other organs. It is also known by exact synonyms such as haemolytic-uraemic syndrome and hemolytic uremic syndrome.

Acute kidney tubular necrosis is a type of acute kidney failure and is a type of condition that at least has the symptom of some necrosis. It is defined as an acute kidney failure that is characterized by necrosis of epithelial tubule cells. Acute kidney tubular necrosis is precisely synonymous with ATN - acute tubular necrosis, acute renal failure with tubular necrosis, acute renal failure with lesion of tubular necrosis, acute tubular necrosis, and acute tubule necrosis.
Duane retraction syndrome is a type of strabismus and has the exact synonyms Duane's syndrome and Stilling-Turk-Duane syndrome.
Chronic progressive external ophthalmoplegia, which has the exact synonym of progressive external ophthalmoplegia, is a type of mitochondrial myopathy.

Idiopathic juvenile osteoporosis is a type of osteoporosis and also falls under the category of conditions that begin during young adult onset. It is defined as an osteoporosis with no known cause, characterized by back and extremities pain, walking difficulties, multiple fractures, and radiological evidence of osteoporosis. Additionally, idiopathic juvenile osteoporosis is exactly synonymous with idiopathic osteoporosis and juvenile osteoporosis.
Ulceration of the vulva is a type of vulvar disease characterized by the presence of ulcers.

Dyscalculia is a type of learning disability defined as a learning disability involving a math disability, which can cause difficulties such as learning math concepts (such as quantity, place value, and time), difficulty memorizing math facts, difficulty organizing numbers, and understanding how problems are organized on the page. Additionally, dyscalculia has exact synonyms including "Mathematics disorder" and "disorder of arithmetical skills."

Phacolytic glaucoma is a type of phacogenic glaucoma and it is defined as a phacogenic glaucoma that is characterized by an acute onset of open-angle glaucoma secondary to a leaking mature or hypermature cataract. This condition has symptoms including chronic progressive vision loss with acute onset of pain, redness, and blurry vision, which are attributed to direct obstruction of aqueous outflow pathways from leaking cataractous lens proteins. Additionally, phacolytic glaucoma has symptoms such as some loss of vision, some bloodshot eye, and some acute pain.

Phacogenic glaucoma is a type of glaucoma characterized by glaucomatous optic atrophy secondary to a lens abnormality. It is defined by symptoms including progressive decreased vision, especially decreased peripheral vision. Causes of phacogenic glaucoma can include cataracts, trauma to the eye, or age-related damage that obstructs aqueous outflow. This obstruction leads to inappropriately increased intraocular pressure, resulting in eventual optic nerve atrophy with associated vision loss.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:neonatal_thyrotoxicosis rdfs:subClassOf :thyrotoxicosis .
text: neonatal thyrotoxicosis is a type of thyrotoxicosis.
Posterior uveitis is a type of panuveitis and it is exactly synonymous with Uveitis, posterior.
Urethral obstruction, which is a type of urethral disease, is exactly synonymous with obstruction of the urethra.

Cri du chat syndrome, also known as 5p deletion syndrome, 5p partial monosomy syndrome, chromosome 5 short arm deletion syndrome, and chromosome 5p deletion syndrome, is a type of chromosomal deletion syndrome and syndrome. It specifically intersects with conditions that have a material basis in some deletion and chromosome. Cri du chat syndrome is defined as a syndrome that is based on the deletion of the end of the chromosome 5 p arm. This condition is characterized by intellectual disability, delayed development, small head size, low birth weight, weak muscle tone, widely set eyes, low-set ears, a small jaw, a rounded face, and a high-pitched cry that resembles that of a cat.

Olecranon bursitis is the same as an intersection of bursitis and a disease that has its location at the olecranon. It is a type of enthesopathy as well as a type of bursitis. Olecranon bursitis is exactly synonymous with several terms, including Bursitis of elbow, Bursitis of elbow region, Capped elbow, Elbow bursitis, Miner's elbow, Miners' elbow, and Shoe boil.

Velocardiofacial syndrome, also precisely known as Shprintzen syndrome and VCF-Velocardiofacial syndrome, is a type of chromosomal deletion syndrome. It is defined as a chromosomal deletion disease with a material basis in a 1.5- to 3.0-Mb hemizygous deletion of chromosome 22q11.2 and characterized by variable developmental problems and schizoid features. Specifically, the haploinsufficiency of the TBX1 gene is responsible for most of the physical malformations associated with this syndrome.

Potter's syndrome is a type of renal agenesis characterized by the typical physical appearance and associated pulmonary hypoplasia of a newborn as a direct result of kidney failure, oligohydramnios, and compression while in the uterus. It also has exact synonyms: Potter sequence and Potter syndrome.
Parametritis is a type of pelvic inflammatory disease and is exactly synonymous with pelvic cellulitis.

Acute leukemia is a type of lymphoid leukemia with a definition as a lymphoid leukemia that occurs when a hematopoietic stem cell undergoes malignant transformation into a primitive, undifferentiated cell with abnormal longevity, resulting in the production of large numbers of white blood cells that enter the bloodstream. Moreover, acute leukemia has exact synonyms, including Stem cell Leukemia and Stem cell leukaemia.

Perineocele is a type of prolapse of the female genital organ, which is defined as a prolapse of the female genital organ characterized by an isolated central defect and herniation of the posterior perineum in patients without diffuse vaginal prolapse.

Hypertrophic pyloric stenosis is a specific type of pyloric stenosis that is characterized by the enlargement of the muscle surrounding the pylorus, leading to severe projectile non-bilious vomiting. This condition is also described as something that invariably presents with the symptom of vomiting. Furthermore, hypertrophic pyloric stenosis is precisely referred to as congenital hypertrophic pyloric stenosis or congenital or infantile stricture of pylorus, indicating exact synonyms for this medical condition.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:pyloric_stenosis rdfs:subClassOf :gastric_outlet_obstruction .
text: pyloric stenosis is a type of gastric outlet obstruction.
The displacement of the cardia through the esophageal hiatus, known exactly as Congenital hiatus hernia, is a type of hiatus hernia.
Hiatus hernia, also known precisely as diaphragmatic hernia and hiatal hernia, is a type of stomach disease.

Vestibulocochlear nerve disease, which has the exact synonym of acoustic nerve disease, is equivalent to conditions that are classified both as a disease and have their location within the vestibulocochlear nerve. Furthermore, this condition is identified as a type of both retrocochlear disease and cranial nerve disease.

Tooth ankylosis is a type of ankylosis and also a type of teeth hard tissue disease. It is identical to a condition that intersects with an ankylosis and a disease that has its location in some calcareous tooth. Moreover, tooth ankylosis has exact synonyms, which include Ankylosis of teeth and Ankylosis of tooth.

Paracoccidioidomycosis, also known exactly as Mucocutaneous-lymphangitic paracoccidioidomycosis and paracoccidioidal mycosis, is a type of primary systemic mycosis. It is defined as a primary systemic mycosis that results in a systemic fungal infection located in various parts of the body, including the mucosa, lymph nodes, bones, skin, or lungs. The disease has its material basis in Paracoccidioides brasiliensis. Furthermore, paracoccidioidomycosis is identified as being the same as an entity that intersects with primary systemic mycosis and an entity that has at least one disease located in any of the following: skin zone, lymph node, mucosa, bone element, or lung.

Blastomycosis is a type of primary systemic mycosis that results in a systemic fungal infection, which is caused by Blastomyces dermatitidis. This condition is transmitted through airborne spores and is characterized by several symptoms, including skin lesions, lung lesions, and pleural thickening. Additionally, blastomycosis is known by several exact synonyms, including Blastomyces Dermatitidis Infection, Blastomycotic infection, Chicago disease, Gilchrist's disease, Infection by Blastomyces dermatitidis, and North American blastomycosis.
Binocular vision disease is a type of strabismus and has an exact synonym, which is simultaneous visual perception without fusion.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:abnormal_retinal_correspondence rdfs:subClassOf :binocular_vision_disease .
text: abnormal retinal correspondence is a type of binocular vision disease.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:hypercalcemia rdfs:subClassOf :calcium_metabolism_disease .
text: hypercalcemia is a type of calcium metabolism disease.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:nephrocalcinosis rdfs:subClassOf :kidney_disease .
text: nephrocalcinosis is a type of kidney disease.

Pseudobulbar palsy, also known exactly as pseudobulbar paralysis, is a type of brain disease characterized by damage to neurons of the corticobulbar tract. It exhibits symptoms such as dysarthria, dysphagia, spasticity located in the tongue, an enhanced gag reflex, and emotional outbursts. This condition represents a form of brain disease that notably includes dysarthria and dysphagia among its symptoms.

Vestibular neuronitis is a type of disease that falls under several categories, including vestibulocochlear nerve disease, poliomyelitis, and conditions that have a material basis in some viruses. It has symptoms such as vertigo, nausea, and vomiting. It is defined as an inner ear infectious disease caused by a viral infection, which involves inflammation of the vestibular nerve, typically resulting as a complication of an upper respiratory infection, leading to sudden and severe vertigo, nausea, and vomiting, while auditory symptoms are usually absent. Additionally, vestibular neuronitis is also known by its exact synonyms, Epidemic neurolabyrinthitis and Vestibular neuritis.

Mixed receptive expressive language disorder is a type of communication disorder characterized by a condition where both the receptive and expressive areas of communication may be affected to any degree, ranging from mild to severe.
Acoustic neuroma is a type of neurilemmoma, and it has exact synonyms: Vestibular Neurilemmoma and Vestibular schwannoma.

Locked-in syndrome is a type of nervous system disease that is defined as a nervous system disease characterized by complete paralysis of all voluntary muscles except for those that control the movements of the eyes. It also has exact synonyms: Locked in syndrome and Locked-in state.

Gynecomastia is a type of disorder of sexual development, defined as a disorder characterized by the enlargement or swelling of male breast tissue. This condition results from elevated male estrogen levels or imbalanced estrogen and testosterone levels.

Leiomyoma is the same as something that is an intersection of a benign neoplasm and something that at least derives from some smooth muscle cell. It is a type of cell type benign neoplasm and is defined as a benign tumor of smooth muscle cells. Moreover, leiomyoma has the exact synonyms "leiomyomatous neoplasm" and "leiomyomatous tumor."

Hereditary Hemorrhagic Telangiectasia (HHT) is a type of autosomal dominant disease, which also falls within the category of vascular diseases. This condition is typified by a genetic background that fundamentally involves autosomal dominant inheritance. HHT is defined as a vascular disease characterized by the existence of multiple arteriovenous malformations that lack intervening capillaries, leading to direct connections between arteries and veins. Furthermore, it is known by exact synonyms such as Osler Hemorrhagic Telangiectasia Syndrome, Osler-Weber-Rendu Disease, and Rendu-Osler-Weber Disease.

Hyperprolactinemia is a type of acquired metabolic disease and is defined as an acquired metabolic disease that has its material basis in the presence of abnormally-high levels of prolactin in the blood. It is exactly synonymous with Chiari-Frommel syndrome, Pregnancy-related A-G syndrome, and hyperprolactinaemia.

Ataxia telangiectasia is a type of autosomal recessive cerebellar ataxia with a definition that outlines it as an autosomal recessive cerebellar ataxia characterized by cerebellar ataxia, telangiectases, immune defects, and a predisposition to malignancy. This condition has a material basis in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the ATM gene on chromosome 11q22. It is exactly synonymous with Boder-Sedgwick syndrome and Louis Bar syndrome. Additionally, ataxia telangiectasia has an exact match with the MESH identifier D001260.

Friedreich ataxia is a type of autosomal recessive cerebellar ataxia, which has several exact synonyms including Friedreich ataxia 1, Friedreich's ataxia, and Friedreich's tabes. Additionally, it has an exact match with MESH:D005621.
Myoclonic cerebellar dyssynergia is a type of neurodegenerative disease, which is also precisely known as Dyssynergia cerebellaris myoclonica and progressive cerebellar tremor.

Capillary disease is synonymous with a condition that is both a type of vascular disease and a disease that specifically affects the capillaries. It is defined as a vascular disease located in the capillaries and is also exactly known as the disease of capillaries.

Black piedra is a type of superficial mycosis, defined as a superficial fungal infection of the hair shaft caused by Piedraia hortae, an ascomycetous fungus. This condition forms hard black nodules on the shafts of the scalp, beard, mustache, and pubic hair.

Nephronophthisis is a type of autosomal recessive disease and a type of kidney disease, which at least has a material basis in some autosomal recessive inheritance. It is defined as a kidney disease characterized by chronic tubulointerstitial nephritis that progresses to terminal renal failure during the second decade (juvenile form) or before the age of 5 years (infantile form), resulting from dysfunction of ciliary proteins (ciliopathy). Furthermore, nephronophthisis has the exact synonyms medullary cystic disease and medullary cystic kidney.

Ellis van Creveld syndrome is a type of syndrome and an autosomal recessive disease, which specifically has a material basis in autosomal recessive inheritance. It is characterized by short limbs, short ribs, postaxial polydactyly, dysplastic nails and teeth, and in many patients, congenital cardiac defects. This syndrome has its material basis in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutations in either the EVC or EVC2 gene on chromosome 4p16.2. Ellis van Creveld syndrome is also exactly synonymous with Chondroectodermal dysplasia and Mesoectodermal dysplasia.

Newborn respiratory distress syndrome is a type of respiratory failure and it is defined as a respiratory failure characterized by a deficiency of the surfactant coating the inner surface of the lungs, the failure of the lungs to expand and contract properly during breathing, resulting in collapse, and the accumulation of a protein-containing film lining the alveoli and their ducts. This syndrome is exactly synonymous with several terms including HMD - Hyaline membrane disease, Neonatal Respiratory Distress Syndrome, hyaline membrane disease, pulmonary hyaline membrane disease, pulmonary hypoperfusion syndrome of newborn, and respiratory distress syndrome of newborn.
Chronic gonococcal salpingitis is a type of chronic salpingitis and is defined as a chronic salpingitis that is caused by gonorrhea. It is exactly synonymous with Gonococcal salpingitis.
Telangiectasis is a type of peripheral vascular disease and has an exact synonym, telangiectasia.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:cerebral_atherosclerosis rdfs:subClassOf :atherosclerosis .
text: cerebral atherosclerosis is a type of atherosclerosis.

Multiple epiphyseal dysplasia, also known precisely as polyepiphyseal dysplasia, is a type of osteochondrodysplasia. It is defined as an osteochondrodysplasia that arises from defective cartilage mineralization into bone, leading to irregular ossification centers located in the hip or knee. This condition is characterized by symptoms such as fatigue and joint pain.

Respiratory syncytial virus infectious disease (RSV), also known exactly as respiratory syncytial virus, is a viral infectious disease. It is characterized by having a material basis in human orthopneumovirus and is transmitted through a combination of droplet spread and vehicle borne fomite transmission. This disease manifests with symptoms including rhinorrhea, wheezing, fever, and cough. RSV is defined as a viral infectious disease resulting in infection located either in the upper respiratory tract or the lower respiratory tract, caused by the Human respiratory syncytial virus. It is transmitted either by droplet spread of nasal secretions from an infected person while coughing or sneezing or by contact with contaminated fomites. The infection is associated with symptoms such as a runny nose, fever, cough, wheezing, and respiratory distress.
Pars planitis is a type of chorioretinitis and has the exact synonym "Posterior cyclitis."
Intermediate uveitis is a type of uveitis that is also known by its exact synonyms, chronic cyclitis and peripheral uveoretinitis.
Hypercementosis is a type of teeth hard tissue disease and is exactly synonymous with Cementation hyperplasia.

Hernia of ovary and fallopian tube is classified as a type of female reproductive system disease. This disease is defined by the protrusion of the ovary and fallopian tube through a defect in the abdominal wall.

Cyclosporiasis is a type of coccidiosis and is defined as a coccidiosis that involves infection of the intestine with the parasitic protozoan Cyclospora cayetanensis, transmitted through contaminated food and water. The disease manifests with several symptoms including watery diarrhea, anorexia, weight loss, abdominal pain, nausea and vomiting, myalgias, low-grade fever, and fatigue.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:corneal_staphyloma rdfs:subClassOf :corneal_disease .
text: corneal staphyloma is a type of corneal disease.
Lacrimal duct cancer, a type of lacrimal system cancer, is also exactly synonymous with malignant neoplasm of the lacrimal duct and malignant tumor of the lacrimal duct.

Choroid cancer is defined as an intersection of something that is both cancer and a disease with a location specifically in the optic choroid. It is categorized as a type of choroid disease and also as a type of uveal cancer. Choroid cancer is precisely synonymous with several terms: Choroidal tumor, choroid neoplasm, malignant tumor of choroid, malignant tumor of the Choroid, and neoplasm of choroid, indicating the various ways it can be referred to within medical terminology without altering its meaning.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:tolosa_hunt_syndrome rdfs:subClassOf :ocular_motility_disease .
text: tolosa hunt syndrome is a type of ocular motility disease.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:cicatricial_ectropion rdfs:subClassOf :ectropion .
text: cicatricial ectropion is a type of ectropion.
Migraine without aura is a type of migraine characterized by migraine headaches that are not accompanied by an aura, which is also exactly synonymous with common migraine.
Diabetic polyneuropathy is a type of diabetic neuropathy, and it has exact synonyms, including Diabetes mellitus with polyneuropathy and Polyneuropathy in diabetes.

Ocular motility disease is synonymous with a condition that is both a type of eye disease and a type of cranial nerve disease, specifically affecting those with any disease located in the eye. Additionally, ocular motility disease is exactly synonymous with "disorder of eye movements" and "eye movement disorder."
Hallucinogen abuse is a type of substance abuse defined as a substance abuse that involves the recurring use of hallucinogenic drugs despite negative consequences.

Mucopolysaccharidosis is a type of lysosomal storage disease, defined as a lysosomal storage disease that involves the accumulation of glycosaminoglycans in the tissues and their excretion in the urine.

Mucopolysaccharidosis II is a type of mucopolysaccharidosis characterized by a deficiency of the lysosomal enzyme iduronate sulfatase. It is also known by several exact synonyms, including Hunter syndrome, Hunter's syndrome, MPS II - Hunter syndrome, Mucopolysaccharidosis, MPS-II, and deficiency of iduronate-2-sulphatase.

Mucopolysaccharidosis VI is a type of mucopolysaccharidosis characterized by a deficiency of the lysosomal enzyme N-acetylgalactosamine 4-sulfatase. It is also known by exact synonyms such as MPS VI - Maroteaux-Lamy syndrome, Maroteaux - Lamy syndrome, Maroteaux-Lamy syndrome, arylsulfatase B deficiency, and deficiency of N-acetylgalactosamine-4-sulfatase.

Mucopolysaccharidosis III is a type of mucopolysaccharidosis that is characterized by a deficiency of the lysosomal enzyme, leading to an incomplete breakdown of the heparan sulfate sugar chain. It is also known by exact synonyms such as Mucopolysaccharidosis, MPS-III, N-sulphoglucosamine sulphohydrolase deficiency, Sanfilippo's syndrome, and heparan sulfate sulfatase deficiency. Additionally, it has a narrow synonym, which is naglu deficiency.

Mucopolysaccharidosis I is a type of mucopolysaccharidosis characterized by a deficiency of the lysosomal enzyme alpha-L-iduronidase. It is also known by several exact synonyms including Hurler syndrome, Hurler-Scheie syndrome, Lipochondrodystrophy, MPS I - Hurler syndrome, Mucopolysaccharidosis, MPS-I, Mucopolysaccharidosis, type 1, and iduronidase deficiency disease.

Sly syndrome is a type of mucopolysaccharidosis defined by a mucopolysaccharidosis characterized by a deficiency of the lysosomal enzyme beta-glucuronidase, resulting in the inability to degrade glucuronic acid-containing glycosaminoglycans. It has exact synonyms including MPS VII - Sly syndrome, beta-glucuronidase deficiency, deficiency of beta-glucuronidase, and mucopolysaccharidosis VII.

Mucopolysaccharidosis IV is a type of mucopolysaccharidosis characterized by a deficiency of the lysosomal enzymes galactose 6-sulfate sulfatase (Type A) or beta-galactosidase (Type B) needed to break down the keratan sulfate sugar chain. It is also known by exact synonyms such as Mucopolysaccharidosis, MPS-IV, deficiency of N-acetylgalactosamine-6-sulphatase, deficiency of chondroitinsulphatase, and galactosamine-6-sulfatase deficiency. Furthermore, mucopolysaccharidosis IV has narrow synonyms including Osteochondrodystrophy and chondroosteodystrophy.

Chronic lacrimal gland enlargement is a type of dacryoadenitis and is also known as chronic enlargement of lacrimal gland. It is a condition that affects the lacrimal gland, indicating that it is a disease located in the lacrimal gland.

Enterocele, also known as vaginal enterocele, is a type of prolapse of the female genital organ. It is defined as a prolapse of the female genital organ characterized by the descent of a peritoneal sac containing small bowel into the rectovaginal space, causing a bulge in the posterior vaginal wall.
Quadriplegia, which has the exact synonym tetraplegia, is a type of central nervous system disease.
Senile entropion, which is a type of entropion, is exactly synonymous with involutional entropion.
Thyroid crisis, which is a type of thyroid gland disease, is also exactly known as Thyrotoxic crisis.

Prolapse of the female genital organ is a type of disease affecting the female reproductive system, characterized by the descent of one or more of the pelvic structures (bladder, uterus, vagina) from their normal anatomic location toward or through the vaginal opening.

Ancylostomiasis is a type of parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that notably affects the skin, eyes, and viscera. This condition is characterized by its material basis in various species of Ancylostoma, including Ancylostoma braziliense, Ancylostoma ceylanicum, Ancylostoma duodenale, or Ancylostoma caninum. Upon infection, the larvae induce lesions on the skin at the penetration site, leading to a range of symptoms such as intestinal and gastrointestinal bleeding, abdominal pain, anemia, severe diarrhea, cachexia, and malnutrition. Furthermore, ancylostomiasis is identified in the medical database with the code MESH:D000724, providing a standardized reference for this disease.

Guillain-Barre syndrome is an autoimmune disease of the peripheral nervous system, which is a type of disease that causes the body's immune system to attack part of the peripheral nervous system. It is also known by several exact synonyms, including Infectious neuronitis, Post-infectious polyneuritis, Postinfectious polyneuritis, acute infective polyneuritis, acute inflammatory demyelinating polyradiculopathy, and acute postinfectious polyneuropathy.

Autistic disorder is a type of autism spectrum disorder characterized by symptoms across all three symptom domains (communication, social, restricted repetitive interests and behaviors), delayed language development, and symptom onset prior to age 3 years. It is also a type of condition that at least has the phenotype of some delayed speech and language development. Autistic disorder is exactly synonymous with Kanner's syndrome, autism, autistic disorder of childhood onset, childhood autism, and infantile autism.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:rectal_disease rdfs:subClassOf :intestinal_disease .
text: rectal disease is a type of intestinal disease.
Achilles bursitis is a type of bursitis that is also exactly synonymous with several conditions, including Achilles bursitis or tendinitis, Capped hock, Haglund's deformity, and Haglund's disease.

Huntington's disease is a type of neurodegenerative disease and is defined as a neurodegenerative disease that is based on autosomal dominant inheritance. It is characterized by unwanted choreatic movements, behavioral and psychiatric disturbances, and dementia. The disease has its material basis in the expansion of CAG triplet repeats (glutamine), resulting in neuron degeneration that affects muscle coordination and cognitive abilities. Huntington's disease is also exactly synonymous with HD, Huntington disease, and Huntington's chorea.

Choreatic disease is a type of movement disease and is defined as a movement disease characterized by brief, semi-directed, irregular movements that are not repetitive or rhythmic, but appear to flow from one muscle to the next. It has exact synonyms, including chorea and hereditary chorea.

Cardiovascular system disease is equivalent to any condition that is both a disease and has a location within the cardiovascular system. It is categorized as a type of disease of anatomical entities. This disease is defined as an ailment of anatomical entities that affects the blood, heart, blood vessels, or the lymphatic system. These components are responsible for transporting nutrients (like amino acids and electrolytes), gases, hormones, blood cells, or lymph throughout the body. This transportation aids in fighting diseases and helps stabilize body temperature and pH to maintain homeostasis. Furthermore, cardiovascular system disease is precisely synonymous with the disease of the subdivision of the hemolymphoid system.

Hypochondriasis is a type of somatoform disorder that is defined as a somatoform disorder involving an excessive preoccupation or worry about having a serious illness. It has exact synonyms including Hypochondria, Hypochondriacal disorder, and Hypochondriacal neurosis.

Miller Fisher Syndrome is a type of Guillain Barre Syndrome that is defined as a Guillain-Barre syndrome manifesting as a descending paralysis, primarily affecting the eye muscles first and characterized by the triad of ophthalmoplegia, ataxia, and areflexia. It is also known by exact synonyms such as Fisher's Syndrome and the Miller-Fisher variant of Guillain-Barre Syndrome.

Neurodegenerative disease is a type of central nervous system disease, which is defined as a central nervous system disease that results in the progressive deterioration of function or structure of neurons. It is also exactly synonymous with degenerative disease.

Sjogren's syndrome is a type of autoimmune disease of the exocrine system, and it can also be described as a condition where the disease is located in the exocrine system. It is defined as an autoimmune disease that involves the attack of immune cells which destroy the exocrine glands that produce tears and saliva. Furthermore, Sjogren's syndrome has exact synonyms, including Sicca syndrome, Sjogren syndrome, and xerodermosteosis.
Keratoconjunctivitis sicca is a type of dry eye syndrome and has the exact synonym KCS.

Submandibular gland disease is the same as a condition that is both a disease and has a location specifically in the submandibular gland. Furthermore, submandibular gland disease is categorized as a type of salivary gland disease.
Benign lymphoepithelial lesion of the salivary gland is a type of salivary gland disease and has an exact synonym, Godwin tumor.

Mikulicz disease is an autoimmune disease characterized by chronic enlargement of the glands of the head and neck. It has symptoms such as lumps of the face and neck, dry eyes, dry mouth, and intermittent fever. This disease is often associated with an underlying autoimmune disorder, hematologic malignancy, tuberculosis infection, or syphilis infection. Mikulicz disease is also known by its exact synonyms, IgG4-related dacryoadenitis and sialadenitis, and Mikulicz's disease. In addition, it is recognized for causing dry mouth as one of its symptoms.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:necrotizing_sialometaplasia rdfs:subClassOf :salivary_gland_disease .
text: necrotizing sialometaplasia is a type of salivary gland disease.
Mucocele of the salivary gland is a type of salivary gland disease and has exact synonyms including Mucous retention cyst of the salivary gland, Ranula, Salivary Cyst, and Salivary gland mucocele.
Sialolithiasis is a type of salivary gland disease, which is exactly synonymous with Salivary Gland Stone, Sialolith, and Stone of salivary gland or duct.

Thromboangiitis obliterans is a type of peripheral vascular disease that is also characterized by at least having the symptom of some gangrene. It has the exact synonyms Buerger's disease and Presenile gangrene.

Plasmodium ovale malaria is defined as a relatively mild form of malaria, caused by the parasite Plasmodium ovale. This form of malaria is characterized by tertian chills and febrile paroxysms and tends to end spontaneously. It is the same as something that is at the intersection of malaria and something that at least has a material basis in Plasmodium ovale. Furthermore, Plasmodium ovale malaria is a type of malaria as well as a type of condition that at least has a material basis in Plasmodium ovale and a type of condition that at least has symptoms including chills. It is also precisely known by the synonyms "Malariaby Plasmodium ovale" and "Ovale malaria."

Hypodermyiasis is a type of myiasis and is defined as a myiasis that involves parasitic infestation of warble flies of the genus Hypoderma on cattle and deer, and Dermatobia hominis on humans. The condition is characterized by the larvae of the human botfly, Dermatobia hominis, feeding in a subdermal cavity, which causes cutaneous swellings on the body or scalp. These swellings may produce discharges and be painful.

Screw worm infectious disease is a type of myiasis that has a definition as a myiasis involving parasitic infestation of Cochliomyia hominivorax or Chrysomya bezziana larvae, which feed on the living tissues of warm-blooded animals. In the case of Cochliomyia infestation, the larvae migrate from the subdermis to other tissues in the body, causing extreme damage. On the other hand, Chrysomya bezziana larvae feed and can cause permanent tissue damage.

Endocardial fibroelastosis is a type of endocardium disease that is characterized by a thickening of the inmost lining of the heart chambers due to an increase in the amount of supporting connective tissue and elastic fibers. It has an exact synonym, Elastomyofibrosis, and also has an exact match with the MESH identifier D004695.

Labia minora carcinoma is a type of vulva carcinoma and has a definition as a vulva carcinoma that is located in the labia minora. It has an exact synonym, Labia Minora cancer, and also a related synonym, carcinoma of labia minora.

Dilated cardiomyopathy is a type of intrinsic cardiomyopathy that is defined by an enlarged heart and damage to the myocardium, causing the heart to pump blood inefficiently. It is exactly synonymous with primary dilated cardiomyopathy. Additionally, dilated cardiomyopathy has related synonyms including Congestive cardiomyopathy, Familial dilated cardiomyopathy, and Idiopathic dilation cardiomyopathy, indicating its association with various conditions.

Endomyocardial fibrosis is a type of restrictive cardiomyopathy and it has several exact synonyms. These synonyms include African endomyocardial fibrosis, Becker's disease, Endomyocardial sclerosis, and obscure African cardiomyopathy.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:kearns_sayre_syndrome rdfs:subClassOf :chronic_progressive_external_ophthalmoplegia .
text: kearns sayre syndrome is a type of chronic progressive external ophthalmoplegia.

Alcoholic cardiomyopathy is a type of extrinsic cardiomyopathy and is also known as Alcohol-induced heart muscle disease or Dilated cardiomyopathy secondary to alcohol. This condition is recognized as a type of disease that is driven at least in part by alcohol.

Vulva carcinoma is a type of vulva cancer and also a type of carcinoma. It is a type of condition that at least derives from some epithelial cell. Specifically, vulva carcinoma is defined as a vulva cancer that has its material basis in abnormally proliferating cells which derive from epithelial cells. It is exactly synonymous with Vulvar carcinoma and is relatedly synonymous with carcinoma of vulva.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:paralytic_lagophthalmos rdfs:subClassOf :lagophthalmos .
text: paralytic lagophthalmos is a type of lagophthalmos.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:lagophthalmos rdfs:subClassOf :eyelid_disease .
text: lagophthalmos is a type of eyelid disease.

Acrocephalosyndactylia is a type of synostosis and is defined as a synostosis that results in craniosynostosis and syndactyly. It has the exact synonym Apert syndrome and has an exact match with MESH:D000168.

Poland syndrome is a type of physical disorder defined as a physical disorder characterized by missing or underdeveloped muscles on one side of the body, leading to abnormalities that can affect the chest, shoulder, arm, and hand. It is also exactly synonymous with Poland's syndactyly.

Subleukemic leukemia is a type of leukemia, defined as a leukemia characterized by the presence of abnormal white blood cells located in the peripheral blood, but in which the total number of white blood cells is normal.

Central nervous system leukemia is a type of central nervous system cancer and is also a type of condition that at least has a material basis in some blood cell. It is a type of disease that is located in the central nervous system. Central nervous system leukemia is defined as a hematologic cancer located in the central nervous system and has an exact synonym, which is Leukemia of the CNS.

Hereditary spherocytosis is a type of congenital hemolytic anemia, which is characterized by the production of red blood cells that have a sphere shape, instead of the normal biconcave disk shape. This condition is also exactly known as Congenital spherocytic hemolytic anemia, Minkowski Chauffard syndrome, and spherocytic anemia.

Intrapelvic lymph node leukemic reticuloendotheliosis is a type of lymph node cancer, which is precisely synonymous with both Leukemic reticuloendotheliosis involving intrapelvic lymph nodes and Leukemic reticuloendotheliosis of intrapelvic lymph nodes.

Plasmodium vivax malaria is identified as a specific form of malaria that intersects with conditions having at least a material basis in Plasmodium vivax. It is classified as a type of malaria and also as a type of condition that fundamentally requires the presence of Plasmodium vivax. The definition of Plasmodium vivax malaria is a malaria caused by the protozoan parasite Plasmodium vivax, which is characterized by inducing fever paroxysms at 48-hour intervals. Additionally, Plasmodium vivax malaria is precisely referred to by the synonyms "Malaria by Plasmodium vivax" and "Vivax Malaria."
Vagus nerve neoplasm is a type of cranial nerve malignant neoplasm. It has exact synonyms including Vagus nerve tumors and neoplasm of vagus nerve.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:leukostasis rdfs:subClassOf :leukocyte_disease .
text: leukostasis is a type of leukocyte disease.

Agranulocytosis is a type of leukopenia and also falls under a category of conditions that at least have the phenotype of some abnormal granulocyte morphology. It is defined as a leukopenia that is characterized by a severe lack of granulocytes, with a drop in granulocyte concentration below 200 cells/mm of blood. Agranulocytosis is exactly synonymous with Granulocytopenic disorder, Granulopenia, and granulocytopenia. Moreover, agranulocytosis has an exact match with MESH:D000380.

Conduct disorder is a type of specific developmental disorder defined as a specific developmental disorder marked by a pattern of repetitive behavior wherein the rights of others or social norms are violated.
Acute dacryocystitis is a type of dacryocystitis and has the exact synonym "Dacryocystitis - acute."

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:phlegmonous_dacryocystitis rdfs:subClassOf :dacryocystitis .
text: phlegmonous dacryocystitis is a type of dacryocystitis.
Carotid stenosis is a type of carotid artery disease, which is exactly synonymous with Carotid artery stenosis and Stenosis, carotid artery.
Subclavian steal syndrome is a type of syndrome that is also exactly known as Subclavian artery stenosis, subclavian steal phenomenon, and subclavian steal steno-occlusive disease.

Vertebrobasilar insufficiency is a type of transient cerebral ischemia and has exact synonyms such as Vertebro-basilar insufficiency, Vertebrobasilar arterial insufficiency, and Vertebrobasilar artery syndrome. Additionally, it has an exact match with the MESH code: D014715.

Intra-abdominal lymph node mast cell malignancy is a specific type of lymph node cancer, mast cell neoplasm, and something that at least derives from some mast cell. It is exactly synonymous with both mast cell malignancy of intra-abdominal lymph nodes and malignant mast cell tumors involving intra-abdominal lymph nodes.
Shipyard eye is a type of keratoconjunctivitis and has exact synonyms EKC and Epidemic keratoconjunctivitis.
Retinopathy of prematurity is a type of retinal disease, which has exact synonyms Retrolental fibroplasia and premature retinopathy.

Lobomycosis is a type of dermatomycosis and also a type of condition that at least has a material basis in some Lacazia loboi. It is defined as a dermatomycosis that results in infection located in the skin or in subcutaneous tissue, has a material basis in Lacazia loboi, and has symptoms including crusty plaques and tumors, ultimately resulting in the formation of nodular lesions. Lobomycosis is exactly synonymous with Cutaneous lobomycosis and infection by Loboa loboi. Additionally, it has a related synonym, Cutaneous blastomycosis.

Transient global amnesia is a type of amnestic disorder, defined as an amnestic disorder characterized by a temporary but almost total disruption of short-term memory along with a range of problems accessing older memories.

:balanoposthitis rdfs:subClassOf :penile_disease .
text: balanoposthitis is a type of penile disease.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:balanitis rdfs:subClassOf :penile_disease .
text: balanitis is a type of penile disease.

Relapsing fever is a primary bacterial infectious disease characterized by infection and has its material basis in Borrelia. It is a type of condition that can be transmitted through tick-borne transmission. The definition of relapsing fever outlines that it results in infection, has its material basis in Borrelia, and is transmitted by either tick or body louse.

Louse-borne relapsing fever is a type of relapsing fever that is also exactly known as Relapsing fever, louse-borne. It is characterized by relapsing or recurring episodes of fever, and its material basis is found in Borrelia recurrentis, which is transmitted by the body louse (Pediculus humanus). This disease is transmitted through insect-borne transmission, specifically by Pediculus humanus. The symptoms of louse-borne relapsing fever include hepatosplenomegaly, enlargement of lymph nodes, tachycardia, tachypnea, relapsing fever, and lymphadenopathy.
